1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:15,000


2
00:00:39,604 --> 00:00:44,735
Look, her first high-end retail
shopping experience.

3
00:00:44,809 --> 00:00:46,606
Her nanny tried
to take her to Baby Gap...

4
00:00:46,677 --> 00:00:48,838
but she'd just cry and cry.

5
00:00:48,913 --> 00:00:51,404
She was a professional shopper
at age three.

6
00:00:51,482 --> 00:00:52,744
Oh, wow!

7
00:00:52,817 --> 00:00:54,910
Remember when she was on
the cover of "Seventeen"?

8
00:00:54,986 --> 00:00:57,511
She had so much potential
back then.

9
00:00:57,588 --> 00:01:00,716
Look at her. She could have been
a Playmate by now.

10
00:01:00,792 --> 00:01:03,352
Hello! She's a lawyer.

11
00:01:03,428 --> 00:01:05,919
- That's way better.
- Why?

12
00:01:05,997 --> 00:01:07,362
There she is!

13
00:01:07,432 --> 00:01:09,923
You always said she has
the perfect shaped head...

14
00:01:10,001 --> 00:01:12,868
for a tiara!

15
00:01:12,937 --> 00:01:15,929
Look at that slime dog!

16
00:01:16,007 --> 00:01:19,704
It was so nice of you to make
this for Elle's wedding shower.

17
00:01:19,777 --> 00:01:22,211
I can't scrapbook worth a damn.

18
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:24,714
I took a class on it
at community college.

19
00:01:24,782 --> 00:01:26,511
- She got a "B."
- Plus!

20
00:01:28,886 --> 00:01:30,854
The day she passed her LSAT!

21
00:01:30,922 --> 00:01:33,254
I swallowed
some of that Silly String.

22
00:01:33,324 --> 00:01:34,655
It wouldn't be the first time.

23
00:01:34,725 --> 00:01:38,252
Look at that.
Her first day at Harvard.

24
00:01:38,329 --> 00:01:40,229
Unbelievable. Awesome.

25
00:01:40,298 --> 00:01:43,665
The Bend and Snap!

26
00:01:43,734 --> 00:01:46,464
I love that.
I did it last night naked.

27
00:01:46,537 --> 00:01:50,064
- You did not.
- Yes. I busted a window.

28
00:01:50,141 --> 00:01:53,838
Oh, my God, there's
Bruiser's first highlights.

29
00:01:53,911 --> 00:01:56,436
Is this the key to
her first office at the firm?

30
00:01:56,514 --> 00:02:00,951
Remember that Caribbean decor?
It was genius.

31
00:02:01,018 --> 00:02:05,614
Look, there she is
with Congresswoman Rudd...

32
00:02:05,690 --> 00:02:08,591
when they started the Harvard
alumni women's event.

33
00:02:08,659 --> 00:02:11,253
- Yeah.
- That's two kick-ass women.

34
00:02:11,329 --> 00:02:14,423
I like them. I really like them.

35
00:02:15,833 --> 00:02:19,132
The first day they met!
Emmett loves her already.

36
00:02:19,203 --> 00:02:21,296
You can see it in his eyes.

37
00:02:21,372 --> 00:02:22,498
Emmett and Elle.

38
00:02:22,573 --> 00:02:26,634
They're truly Romeo and Juliet
without the dying.

39
00:02:26,711 --> 00:02:28,008
Paulette?

40
00:02:28,079 --> 00:02:30,274
Oh, my God!
Girls, I think it's her.

41
00:02:30,348 --> 00:02:32,782
- Quick! Lights out!
- OK!

42
00:02:36,153 --> 00:02:38,314
Paulette?

43
00:02:38,389 --> 00:02:41,825
I thought we were supposed
to be at the movies by 9:00.

44
00:02:41,893 --> 00:02:44,862
Surprise!

45
00:02:51,402 --> 00:02:53,199
We got her!

46
00:02:53,271 --> 00:02:55,603
Oh, my God! Margot, Serena,
I cannot believe...

47
00:02:55,673 --> 00:02:57,334
you guys flew
all the way here!

48
00:02:57,408 --> 00:02:59,808
- No biggie.
- On the contrary.

49
00:02:59,877 --> 00:03:01,811
It's a huge biggie.
Thank you.

50
00:03:01,879 --> 00:03:03,642
You guys are the best.

51
00:03:03,714 --> 00:03:07,844
Speaking of biggies,
can we see your ring again?

52
00:03:07,919 --> 00:03:11,252
Not your Delta Nu ring, Elle.

53
00:03:11,322 --> 00:03:13,984
You mean, this one?

54
00:03:16,193 --> 00:03:19,526
Clarity between F.L. And V.V.S.
Nice girdle diameter.

55
00:03:19,597 --> 00:03:22,031
Cut impeccable.
It's a keeper.

56
00:03:22,099 --> 00:03:24,329
Thanks!

57
00:03:24,402 --> 00:03:27,269
Oh, my gosh, it's from Emmett!

58
00:03:27,338 --> 00:03:30,535
That's me and Emmett
on Fenway baseball field.

59
00:03:30,608 --> 00:03:32,269
It's his favorite place
in the whole world.

60
00:03:32,343 --> 00:03:35,471
I love snow globes.

61
00:03:36,614 --> 00:03:38,912
I can hear the ocean.

62
00:03:38,983 --> 00:03:41,918
Listen, honey,
you're a full-time bride now...

63
00:03:41,986 --> 00:03:43,783
so you'll need
a whole new wardrobe.

64
00:03:43,854 --> 00:03:47,085
I'm not quitting my job,
you guys.

65
00:03:47,158 --> 00:03:49,217
Do you guys remember
that feeling we used to get...

66
00:03:49,293 --> 00:03:51,420
during a really intense
Spinning class?

67
00:03:51,495 --> 00:03:55,693
That we feel so truly amazing
about ourselves?

68
00:03:55,766 --> 00:03:58,462
That's how I feel
being a lawyer. I love it.

69
00:03:58,536 --> 00:04:01,528
I have this huge
annual review coming up...

70
00:04:01,606 --> 00:04:03,801
so keep 'em crossed, girls.

71
00:04:03,874 --> 00:04:05,398
Crossed!

72
00:04:07,445 --> 00:04:09,606
Congratulations, you did it.

73
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:13,639
With three wrong answers,
you've managed to undermine...

74
00:04:13,718 --> 00:04:17,984
the entire foundation upon which
our legal system's built.

75
00:04:18,055 --> 00:04:21,422
And by the way...

76
00:04:21,492 --> 00:04:24,017
it only took me
two wrong answers.

77
00:04:31,669 --> 00:04:36,231
Sweetie, you customized my ring?
Again?

78
00:04:36,307 --> 00:04:39,071
Emmett, you are never
going to believe my news!

79
00:04:39,143 --> 00:04:41,270
- What?
- Fenway Park!

80
00:04:41,345 --> 00:04:44,337
You, me, two rings, and
one recently ordained umpire...

81
00:04:44,415 --> 00:04:45,643
right on the entry field!

82
00:04:45,716 --> 00:04:47,741
Infield.
What are you talking about?

83
00:04:47,818 --> 00:04:50,116
It turns out the starting
pitcher for the Red Sox...

84
00:04:50,187 --> 00:04:52,314
has an unfortunate
unibrow problem.

85
00:04:52,390 --> 00:04:54,449
He goes to Nadia, my waxer...

86
00:04:54,525 --> 00:04:56,356
so the team pulled some strings
with the site manager...

87
00:04:56,427 --> 00:04:58,088
and we're getting married
at Fenway!

88
00:04:58,162 --> 00:05:00,653
Are you serious?

89
00:05:00,731 --> 00:05:03,962
Are you sure
this is what you want to do?

90
00:05:04,035 --> 00:05:07,698
I can married anywhere
and it wouldn't matter.

91
00:05:07,772 --> 00:05:09,603
That's a lie.

92
00:05:09,674 --> 00:05:14,373
I'm getting married
under the Green Monster!

93
00:05:14,445 --> 00:05:16,436
Yes!

94
00:05:16,514 --> 00:05:18,482
And in just
three months and four days!

95
00:05:18,549 --> 00:05:20,813
Emmett, we have so much
to talk about.

96
00:05:20,885 --> 00:05:23,854
I want everybody
who matters to us to be there.

97
00:05:25,790 --> 00:05:28,554
Oh, my God! I almost forgot!

98
00:05:30,294 --> 00:05:31,228
You want me to what?

99
00:05:31,228 --> 00:05:32,559
You want me to what?

100
00:05:32,630 --> 00:05:35,190
A biological
birth parent search.

101
00:05:35,266 --> 00:05:37,131
For your dog.

102
00:05:37,201 --> 00:05:40,568
For my Chihuahua-American
Bruiser Woods.

103
00:05:40,638 --> 00:05:44,233
I found him abandoned years ago.

104
00:05:44,308 --> 00:05:48,039
Miss, I'm the highest-paid,
most sought after...

105
00:05:48,112 --> 00:05:51,172
private investigator
in the greater Boston area.

106
00:05:51,248 --> 00:05:52,875
That's precisely why
we came to you, Detective.

107
00:05:52,950 --> 00:05:56,647
It is absolutely vital that
we find Bruiser's mother pronto.

108
00:05:56,721 --> 00:06:00,987
His father might be
more difficult. You know dogs.

109
00:06:01,058 --> 00:06:02,423
May I ask why?

110
00:06:02,493 --> 00:06:04,427
Of course.
"Martha Stewart Weddings"...

111
00:06:04,495 --> 00:06:07,362
recommends a 4 to 6-week
window for RSVPs...

112
00:06:07,431 --> 00:06:09,956
and I can't send the invitation
without an address.

113
00:06:10,034 --> 00:06:13,401
And the sooner I get started on
the calligraphy the better.

114
00:06:13,471 --> 00:06:16,406
You want to send an invitation
to your wedding...

115
00:06:16,474 --> 00:06:19,034
to your dog's mother.
And you're serious?

116
00:06:19,110 --> 00:06:20,441
Detective,
if I have to make room...

117
00:06:20,511 --> 00:06:22,445
for my second cousin's
vegan diet coach...

118
00:06:22,513 --> 00:06:24,242
you better believe
I'll make room for the mother...

119
00:06:24,315 --> 00:06:27,011
of the one loving creature
who's always been there for me.

120
00:06:27,084 --> 00:06:30,212
In fact, I can't believe
I haven't done this sooner!

121
00:06:30,287 --> 00:06:33,051
I'm thinking the same thing.

122
00:06:40,264 --> 00:06:42,095
- Elle!
- Hi, Mr. Blaine.

123
00:06:42,166 --> 00:06:44,430
- The client is thrilled.
- Good!

124
00:06:44,502 --> 00:06:46,902
How you seamlessly
negotiated that deal?

125
00:06:46,971 --> 00:06:50,407
- It was simply magnifique.
- Thank you.

126
00:06:50,474 --> 00:06:51,702
Big staff meeting today, kiddo.

127
00:06:51,776 --> 00:06:55,337
All right.
I got my fingers crossed.

128
00:06:55,412 --> 00:06:57,846
Milton, two shots, extra foam.

129
00:06:57,915 --> 00:07:00,577
- Wow. Thanks, E.W.
- No problem!

130
00:07:00,651 --> 00:07:02,915
- Go get 'em today.
- Thanks.

131
00:07:02,987 --> 00:07:04,955
Soy for you, honey. No dairy.

132
00:07:05,022 --> 00:07:06,853
That's right. Thank you.
Your call list is endless.

133
00:07:06,924 --> 00:07:08,892
- It is?
- We better get right on it.

134
00:07:10,427 --> 00:07:12,918
Kevin, you shouldn't have!

135
00:07:12,997 --> 00:07:15,465
I'm not sure they're giving me
the promotion today.

136
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:17,467
It's just a widespread
yet credible rumor.

137
00:07:17,535 --> 00:07:20,060
It's from me and the girls.

138
00:07:20,137 --> 00:07:21,832
Oh, right!

139
00:07:23,974 --> 00:07:25,498
Now do me.

140
00:07:28,879 --> 00:07:31,143
I feel like the luckiest girl
in the world.

141
00:07:31,215 --> 00:07:32,944
- Me, too!
- You do?

142
00:07:33,017 --> 00:07:35,076
I had no idea
I could be this happy...

143
00:07:35,152 --> 00:07:38,019
without accruing
credit card debt.

144
00:07:38,088 --> 00:07:39,851
Already?

145
00:07:39,924 --> 00:07:43,291
Well, Miss Woods,
even the weird ones get cracked.

146
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:46,124
- You ready?
- Yes!

147
00:07:48,432 --> 00:07:51,026
Bruiser Woods...

148
00:07:51,101 --> 00:07:53,626
meet your mom.

149
00:07:53,704 --> 00:07:56,502
Bruiser... your cheekbones.

150
00:07:58,442 --> 00:07:59,875
And it's all in there.

151
00:07:59,944 --> 00:08:02,412
Good luck finding whatever
it is you're looking for.

152
00:08:04,148 --> 00:08:07,606
Oh, my God!
She's a Bostonian!

153
00:08:10,254 --> 00:08:13,382
Bruiser, we're here!

154
00:08:13,457 --> 00:08:15,288
As your adoptive mother,
I'm sure you're nervous...

155
00:08:15,359 --> 00:08:16,792
about meeting
your birth mother...

156
00:08:16,861 --> 00:08:21,423
but hear her out, OK?
I'm sure she had her reasons.

157
00:08:21,498 --> 00:08:23,898
Bruiser,
your mother lives at...

158
00:08:23,968 --> 00:08:25,697
the top secret
Versace think-tank!

159
00:08:25,769 --> 00:08:27,828
I told you they had one!

160
00:08:27,905 --> 00:08:29,031
No, ma'am.

161
00:08:29,106 --> 00:08:31,336
Unless you have a pass,
you cannot go up there.

162
00:08:31,408 --> 00:08:33,342
Lucky I always keep it on me.

163
00:08:33,410 --> 00:08:36,811
Hold on. It's right here.

164
00:08:36,881 --> 00:08:38,542
There you go.

165
00:08:38,616 --> 00:08:40,675
What is it?

166
00:08:40,751 --> 00:08:42,378
It's my double platinum
V.V.I.P. Versace...

167
00:08:42,453 --> 00:08:44,512
Preferred Customer
identification card.

168
00:08:44,588 --> 00:08:47,819
Available only to those that've
shopped on five continents.

169
00:08:47,892 --> 00:08:49,723
If that fails to satisfy you,
you can also contact...

170
00:08:49,793 --> 00:08:52,353
Billy Dailey,
head of customer relations.

171
00:08:52,429 --> 00:08:53,760
You got the wrong VERSACE, lady.

172
00:08:53,831 --> 00:08:55,992
Really? Donatella's not here?

173
00:08:56,066 --> 00:08:57,363
Bruiser, where are you going?

174
00:08:57,434 --> 00:08:59,527
Bruiser!

175
00:08:59,603 --> 00:09:00,900
Ma'am!

176
00:09:03,741 --> 00:09:04,935
Bruiser?

177
00:09:05,009 --> 00:09:07,477
Get back here!

178
00:09:07,544 --> 00:09:09,603
Where are you going?

179
00:09:11,982 --> 00:09:15,543
Bruiser, I didn't know
you were so athletic.

180
00:09:21,025 --> 00:09:23,994
What is it?

181
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:30,430
Oh, my God!

182
00:09:34,538 --> 00:09:37,439
You, come here!

183
00:09:37,508 --> 00:09:40,602
Come on!
Open this door immediately!

184
00:09:40,678 --> 00:09:41,872
What are you doing here?

185
00:09:41,946 --> 00:09:46,645
You have my dog's mom,
and I need her right now!

186
00:09:46,717 --> 00:09:48,742
Absolutely not.
I'm not authorized to release...

187
00:09:48,819 --> 00:09:50,787
any subjects
from their containment units.

188
00:09:50,854 --> 00:09:53,755
I'm not even allowed
to have a key.

189
00:09:53,824 --> 00:09:55,849
Swallow the thing one time,
and all of a sudden...

190
00:09:55,926 --> 00:09:58,827
you're the weird key swallower
who can't be trusted.

191
00:10:00,297 --> 00:10:02,891
I don't think
you're understanding me.

192
00:10:02,967 --> 00:10:04,434
I'm willing to pay for her.

193
00:10:04,501 --> 00:10:06,093
These animals
aren't for sale, ma'am.

194
00:10:06,170 --> 00:10:07,899
They're the legal property
of this facility.

195
00:10:07,972 --> 00:10:11,271
What kind of facility is this?

196
00:10:14,611 --> 00:10:16,408
Mr. Livermore, I'm so sorry!

197
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:19,881
Elle, this VERSACE
is a cosmetic testing facility.

198
00:10:19,950 --> 00:10:23,113
- Oh, no!
- Bruiser's mom's a test subject.

199
00:10:23,187 --> 00:10:25,018
I want her out of there
immediately.

200
00:10:25,089 --> 00:10:27,114
Animal test subjects
can only be surrendered...

201
00:10:27,191 --> 00:10:29,523
on a voluntary basis,
and they're not volunteering.

202
00:10:29,593 --> 00:10:32,118
After I get through with them,
they'll be begging.

203
00:10:32,196 --> 00:10:33,629
And I'm not just taking
Bruiser's mom.

204
00:10:33,697 --> 00:10:36,666
I'll bust all those dogs
out of that doggie dungeon.

205
00:10:36,734 --> 00:10:39,066
"Research Science
and Critter Exploitation"?

206
00:10:39,136 --> 00:10:42,299
This VERSACE's owned by the
C'est Magnifique Corporation!

207
00:10:42,373 --> 00:10:44,000
That's fantastic!

208
00:10:44,074 --> 00:10:46,474
Our law firm
represents C'est Magnifique.

209
00:10:46,543 --> 00:10:48,170
We can tell them to fix this.

210
00:10:48,245 --> 00:10:50,770
I can't wait to take this
to the partners.

211
00:10:50,848 --> 00:10:53,942
But how are you
going to convince them?

212
00:10:54,018 --> 00:10:55,986
Presenting...

213
00:10:59,123 --> 00:11:03,219
Abandoned at birth, I was
on my own at an early age...

214
00:11:03,293 --> 00:11:08,162
fighting for survival on
the streets of Beverly Hills...

215
00:11:08,232 --> 00:11:11,633
making his way down
the boulevard of broken dreams,

216
00:11:11,702 --> 00:11:15,035
turning tricks
at Hollywood and Vine...

217
00:11:15,105 --> 00:11:17,437
yet even when
I found a loving mother...

218
00:11:17,508 --> 00:11:20,909
I couldn't shake this
nagging emptiness in my heart.

219
00:11:20,978 --> 00:11:23,606
It was like a void.
When I looked in the mirror...

220
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:25,671
who was it
that was looking back at me?

221
00:11:25,749 --> 00:11:28,240
This is Bruiser's question.

222
00:11:28,318 --> 00:11:32,345
And in a way,
aren't we all Bruisers?

223
00:11:32,423 --> 00:11:35,688
I think yes. Thank you.

224
00:11:38,095 --> 00:11:40,825
Ms. Woods,
this is a law firm...

225
00:11:40,898 --> 00:11:43,696
not an animal rights
advocacy group.

226
00:11:43,767 --> 00:11:46,201
We're lawyers.
We have to fight for justice.

227
00:11:46,270 --> 00:11:48,204
And this is definitely unjust.

228
00:11:48,272 --> 00:11:52,038
In this case, the cost of beauty
is way too high.

229
00:11:52,109 --> 00:11:54,475
I can't believe I said that,
but it's true.

230
00:11:54,545 --> 00:11:56,604
What we fight for...

231
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,978
is our clients
and their best interests.

232
00:11:59,049 --> 00:12:02,746
But isn't doing the right thing
in everybody's best interest?

233
00:12:02,820 --> 00:12:05,812
I think you're confusing
the right thing and the law.

234
00:12:05,889 --> 00:12:09,552
You didn't think
they were the same, did you?

235
00:12:09,626 --> 00:12:12,686
Why don't
we get back to business...

236
00:12:12,763 --> 00:12:15,254
and discuss
your very bright future?

237
00:12:15,332 --> 00:12:17,323
Pardon me,
I don't mean to interrupt...

238
00:12:17,401 --> 00:12:20,802
but I just--
What you're saying is...

239
00:12:20,871 --> 00:12:23,499
if C'est Magnifique
follows the letter of the law...

240
00:12:23,574 --> 00:12:27,010
even if it ends up
hurting living beings...

241
00:12:27,077 --> 00:12:31,275
we're just doing our job?

242
00:12:31,348 --> 00:12:35,079
I'm sorry, Mr. Blaine...

243
00:12:35,152 --> 00:12:38,485
I don't think I can work
with people who believe that.

244
00:12:40,858 --> 00:12:44,658
You know what? You're right.

245
00:12:44,728 --> 00:12:46,992
Thank you, Mr. Blaine.

246
00:12:47,064 --> 00:12:49,259
You shouldn't have to work
with people who believe that.

247
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:51,392
Absolutely.
I knew you would understand.

248
00:12:51,468 --> 00:12:53,732
You're fired, Elle.

249
00:12:53,804 --> 00:12:55,294
What?

250
00:12:55,372 --> 00:12:59,138
We only have room
for serious lawyers here.

251
00:12:59,209 --> 00:13:03,077
Take the rest of the day
to clear out your things.

252
00:13:03,147 --> 00:13:07,140
But the secretarial pool
already gave me a balloon.

253
00:13:07,217 --> 00:13:09,708
Keep the balloon, if you wish.

254
00:13:20,297 --> 00:13:22,765
Please, Emmett, just go away.

255
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:25,131
Why don't you come on out,
sweetie?

256
00:13:25,202 --> 00:13:27,295
I know Bruiser
doesn't blame you.

257
00:13:27,371 --> 00:13:30,238
But I'm all he has to speak
for him in this world...

258
00:13:30,307 --> 00:13:31,774
and I have
completely failed him.

259
00:13:31,842 --> 00:13:35,835
You know what I thought
the first time I saw you?

260
00:13:35,913 --> 00:13:39,314
"God, that woman
wears a lot of pink"?

261
00:13:39,383 --> 00:13:43,581
No. I thought...

262
00:13:43,654 --> 00:13:46,248
"That woman is really special."

263
00:13:46,323 --> 00:13:50,657
"She believes she can make
a difference and she will."

264
00:13:50,727 --> 00:13:55,562
So... come on out
and let's talk about it.

265
00:13:55,632 --> 00:13:57,657
No.

266
00:13:57,734 --> 00:14:01,534
We could go over
some wedding details.

267
00:14:04,408 --> 00:14:06,842
How about that? It revolves.

268
00:14:06,910 --> 00:14:08,207
And it illuminates.

269
00:14:08,278 --> 00:14:10,610
It's even
got the Red Sox colors.

270
00:14:10,681 --> 00:14:13,081
That's fantastic, honey!

271
00:14:13,150 --> 00:14:15,311
Speaking of red socks...

272
00:14:15,385 --> 00:14:17,250
you're not getting
cold feet, are you?

273
00:14:17,321 --> 00:14:18,549
About what?

274
00:14:18,622 --> 00:14:21,250
How's it going to look?
A Harvard law professor...

275
00:14:21,325 --> 00:14:23,793
married to a lawyer who
got fired from her first job.

276
00:14:23,860 --> 00:14:25,851
Fired for something
she believes in.

277
00:14:25,929 --> 00:14:27,487
It's going to look like...

278
00:14:27,564 --> 00:14:32,695
"There goes the luckiest guy
in the whole world."

279
00:14:33,804 --> 00:14:35,829
Thanks.

280
00:14:43,614 --> 00:14:46,606
Holy crap!

281
00:14:46,683 --> 00:14:50,744
It's gorgeous!

282
00:14:50,821 --> 00:14:52,846
The material
keeps falling apart.

283
00:14:52,923 --> 00:14:54,447
No!

284
00:14:54,524 --> 00:14:56,719
Amy, is something wrong?

285
00:14:58,929 --> 00:15:01,454
You can't do a scallop trim
on the outer hoop skirt.

286
00:15:01,531 --> 00:15:04,364
The material's too delicate.
It'll just fall apart.

287
00:15:04,434 --> 00:15:06,664
But in two out of three
home tests it held.

288
00:15:06,737 --> 00:15:08,728
I am so sorry, Elle.

289
00:15:13,176 --> 00:15:15,701
No biggie.
I guess I don't need...

290
00:15:15,779 --> 00:15:18,646
a scallop trim
on the outer hoop skirt.

291
00:15:18,715 --> 00:15:20,808
I'll be fine.

292
00:15:20,884 --> 00:15:22,818
What is it that you said
back when I couldn't...

293
00:15:22,886 --> 00:15:26,720
fit into my white spandex
pantsuit for my wedding?

294
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:28,314
If the fabric
doesn't work with you...

295
00:15:28,392 --> 00:15:30,121
don't work with it.

296
00:15:30,193 --> 00:15:31,353
It's one of
my favorite mantras.

297
00:15:31,428 --> 00:15:34,829
That is so true, and I know
the most perfect organza!

298
00:15:34,898 --> 00:15:37,833
Or something
really classy like...

299
00:15:37,901 --> 00:15:40,426
like white leather!

300
00:15:40,504 --> 00:15:43,667
I'll call the guy
that did my car seats.

301
00:15:43,740 --> 00:15:47,141
Wait... that's it.

302
00:15:47,210 --> 00:15:51,613
Don't fight the fabric.
Change it.

303
00:15:51,682 --> 00:15:54,515
OK, but white leather?

304
00:15:56,086 --> 00:15:59,419
If the law is what's keeping
Bruiser's mother locked up...

305
00:15:59,489 --> 00:16:01,787
I shouldn't be fighting it,
I should be changing it.

306
00:16:01,858 --> 00:16:04,759
Everybody, I'm going to make...

307
00:16:04,828 --> 00:16:07,160
animal testing
for cosmetics illegal!

308
00:16:07,230 --> 00:16:10,996
I know that making a dog wear
mascara and blush is wrong...

309
00:16:11,068 --> 00:16:12,933
This isn't just about
Bruiser's mom anymore...

310
00:16:13,003 --> 00:16:14,561
this is about the fact
that every day...

311
00:16:14,638 --> 00:16:16,936
that I put on my Gold Goddess
luminescent blush...

312
00:16:17,007 --> 00:16:20,204
some poor little innocent animal
might be suffering for it.

313
00:16:20,277 --> 00:16:22,404
You don't realize
how horrible something is...

314
00:16:22,479 --> 00:16:24,106
until it happens to you
personally.

315
00:16:24,181 --> 00:16:25,978
Like breastfeeding.

316
00:16:26,049 --> 00:16:28,779
And if I want to give
a voice to Bruiser...

317
00:16:28,852 --> 00:16:31,184
I have to go to the place
that gave a voice to the people!

318
00:16:31,254 --> 00:16:36,157
Oh, my God! The headquarters
of "Cosmopolitan" magazine!

319
00:16:37,761 --> 00:16:40,457
Better! Ladies...

320
00:16:40,530 --> 00:16:42,589
I'm going to Washington!

321
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,126
D.C., here I come!

322
00:16:45,202 --> 00:16:47,670
If anybody can handle this,
it's you, honey.

323
00:16:47,738 --> 00:16:51,265
I got a call from the Delta Nu
24-hour housing hotline.

324
00:16:51,341 --> 00:16:52,706
Your apartment's all set.

325
00:16:52,776 --> 00:16:55,108
- Great!
- Elle!

326
00:16:56,613 --> 00:17:01,710
Oh, my God! You look like
the Fourth of July!

327
00:17:01,785 --> 00:17:05,221
Makes me want a hot dog
real bad.

328
00:17:05,288 --> 00:17:08,724
Yeah, OK.
You got to get going, honey.

329
00:17:08,792 --> 00:17:09,952
OK.

330
00:17:11,495 --> 00:17:13,429
- Elle, look at this.
- What's that?

331
00:17:13,497 --> 00:17:15,465
According to
"Animal Fair" magazine...

332
00:17:15,532 --> 00:17:18,399
your new boss is the best
groomed woman in Washington.

333
00:17:18,468 --> 00:17:20,868
Her beagle's name
is Dolly Madison...

334
00:17:20,937 --> 00:17:24,373
which is my grandma's
stripper name.

335
00:17:24,441 --> 00:17:26,204
Isn't that a good sign?

336
00:17:26,276 --> 00:17:27,971
Oh, my gosh. A job with
a brilliant congresswoman...

337
00:17:28,044 --> 00:17:29,375
who's also
a fellow Harvard alum.

338
00:17:29,446 --> 00:17:32,609
You'll do great, Elle.
It's destiny.

339
00:17:32,682 --> 00:17:34,809
But isn't planning
the wedding of the century...

340
00:17:34,885 --> 00:17:37,979
and changing the law
kind of hard?

341
00:17:38,054 --> 00:17:40,648
Paulette, I taught Bruiser
how to shop online.

342
00:17:40,724 --> 00:17:43,693
I think I can handle Congress.

343
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:46,160
See ya.

344
00:18:24,234 --> 00:18:26,600
Home sweet home. You ready?

345
00:18:26,670 --> 00:18:28,069
OK.

346
00:18:28,138 --> 00:18:29,571
Welcome to
the Wellington, ma'am.

347
00:18:29,639 --> 00:18:31,698
It's a thrill to be here!

348
00:18:50,794 --> 00:18:52,785
Time to legislate!

349
00:18:54,998 --> 00:18:56,465
No.

350
00:19:00,337 --> 00:19:02,328
Too Nancy.

351
00:19:02,405 --> 00:19:04,669
Too Hillary.

352
00:19:04,741 --> 00:19:07,539
Too Monica.

353
00:19:07,611 --> 00:19:10,375
Too perfect for words!

354
00:19:16,152 --> 00:19:18,017
Hi!

355
00:19:18,088 --> 00:19:20,852
Good morning,
fellow public servants.

356
00:19:20,924 --> 00:19:22,687
It's my first day.

357
00:19:27,230 --> 00:19:28,390
Nice briefcase.

358
00:19:28,465 --> 00:19:30,990
Huh? Thank you.

359
00:19:33,503 --> 00:19:35,164
Hi!

360
00:19:39,809 --> 00:19:44,007
Last item on
our agenda--Elle Woods.

361
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:46,105
Personal Rudd hire,
taking up a bill...

362
00:19:46,182 --> 00:19:48,912
on animal testing
in the cosmetic industry.

363
00:19:48,985 --> 00:19:50,714
I'm sorry,
Rudd's backing that?

364
00:19:50,787 --> 00:19:52,277
Matter of conscience,
whatever.

365
00:19:52,355 --> 00:19:55,085
Who knows? Maybe it'll boost
our female demographic.

366
00:19:55,158 --> 00:19:57,058
The point is
we're animal lovers now.

367
00:19:57,127 --> 00:20:00,961
If this is so important to Rudd,
shouldn't I be handling it?

368
00:20:01,031 --> 00:20:03,864
No, Timothy,
not when we have a woman...

369
00:20:03,934 --> 00:20:05,868
who according to Rudd,
is one of the shrewdest...

370
00:20:05,936 --> 00:20:08,131
legal and political minds
of our time.

371
00:20:10,273 --> 00:20:13,606
Hello, patriots!

372
00:20:13,677 --> 00:20:15,144
I don't think
I've been this excited...

373
00:20:15,211 --> 00:20:17,406
since Gucci became
a publicly traded company.

374
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:21,041
Oh, my God,
it's Capitol Barbie.

375
00:20:21,117 --> 00:20:23,244
She's so shiny.

376
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:25,220
So where should I start?

377
00:20:25,288 --> 00:20:26,755
Excuse me, sweetie?

378
00:20:26,823 --> 00:20:30,418
Intern orientation
is down the hall in Room 216.

379
00:20:30,493 --> 00:20:34,224
That's before 217 and after 215.

380
00:20:34,297 --> 00:20:36,595
Oh, my God!
That is so sweet of you!

381
00:20:36,666 --> 00:20:38,463
You think I'm an intern?

382
00:20:38,535 --> 00:20:41,470
That anti-wrinkle
all-salmon diet really works.

383
00:20:41,538 --> 00:20:42,732
Who are you?

384
00:20:42,806 --> 00:20:47,368
- I'm sorry--
- Elle Woods, welcome!

385
00:20:47,444 --> 00:20:50,004
I haven't seen you
since the alumni meeting!

386
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:53,311
- I know! How are you?
- Good!

387
00:20:53,383 --> 00:20:55,374
This is Elle Woods, everyone.

388
00:20:55,452 --> 00:20:58,717
Basically me
when I first came to D. C...

389
00:20:58,788 --> 00:21:01,882
so make her feel at home.

390
00:21:01,958 --> 00:21:03,516
You ready to hit
the ground running?

391
00:21:03,593 --> 00:21:05,618
Are these not
my comfortable heels?

392
00:21:05,695 --> 00:21:09,756
- Cute shoes.
- Thank you. They are comfy.

393
00:21:11,101 --> 00:21:13,592
Here's Bruiser. Welcome.

394
00:21:15,071 --> 00:21:18,268
Oh, you little sugar!

395
00:21:18,341 --> 00:21:20,070
Back her up, people.

396
00:21:20,143 --> 00:21:23,010
This is the most collaborative
bunch on the Hill...

397
00:21:23,079 --> 00:21:24,706
So gather them together...

398
00:21:24,781 --> 00:21:26,749
talk strategy as soon as
you get settled in.

399
00:21:26,816 --> 00:21:28,374
- And, Elle?
- Yes?

400
00:21:28,451 --> 00:21:31,477
- Welcome to Washington.
- Thank you!

401
00:21:31,554 --> 00:21:34,489
Okey-dokey.

402
00:21:34,557 --> 00:21:37,458
I missed the part about
where my office is.

403
00:21:37,527 --> 00:21:40,360
The desk. Right here.

404
00:21:43,667 --> 00:21:47,068
All righty. Then I'm going
to need a glue gun...

405
00:21:47,137 --> 00:21:51,233
some pinking shears, and
five yards of grosgrain ribbon.

406
00:21:51,307 --> 00:21:53,298
Yeah, that'll do it.

407
00:21:56,413 --> 00:21:58,745
Well, look at you.

408
00:21:58,815 --> 00:22:00,806
You can run your wedding
coordinator business...

409
00:22:00,884 --> 00:22:02,715
during all that
legislative downtime.

410
00:22:02,786 --> 00:22:04,276
Don't be silly, Grace.

411
00:22:04,354 --> 00:22:06,584
This is to plan
my own wedding to Emmett.

412
00:22:06,656 --> 00:22:09,318
See, this is us.
He had this made for me.

413
00:22:09,392 --> 00:22:12,555
That's him,
and that's me smiling.

414
00:22:12,629 --> 00:22:13,994
Maybe he'll make one
of you and me.

415
00:22:14,064 --> 00:22:15,827
You'll be talking
and I'll be throwing up.

416
00:22:15,899 --> 00:22:18,367
Speaking of nuptials,
wait till I tell...

417
00:22:18,435 --> 00:22:20,096
the congresswoman
that I was invited...

418
00:22:20,170 --> 00:22:22,104
to John McCain's
nephew's wedding.

419
00:22:22,172 --> 00:22:24,037
He's really quite a sweet kid.

420
00:22:24,107 --> 00:22:25,699
Tell me something, Timothy...

421
00:22:25,775 --> 00:22:28,335
is it difficult for you
to breathe with...

422
00:22:28,411 --> 00:22:30,572
your mouth flat
against your employer's butt?

423
00:22:30,647 --> 00:22:33,275
I don't know, Grace.
Is it difficult to see...

424
00:22:33,349 --> 00:22:35,408
with your head in
the Minority Whip's lap?

425
00:22:35,485 --> 00:22:37,715
It was the distinguished
gentlemen from Iowa.

426
00:22:37,787 --> 00:22:40,449
His wife had recently left him
and we just talked.

427
00:22:40,523 --> 00:22:43,492
Right. Because if
you did "visit" his district...

428
00:22:43,560 --> 00:22:45,994
you should've gotten
some legislation out of it.

429
00:22:46,062 --> 00:22:47,188
How would you even know...

430
00:22:47,263 --> 00:22:49,731
when you're busy chasing
interns on a skateboard?

431
00:22:49,799 --> 00:22:52,666
Excuse me? Who wants
to talk animal testing?

432
00:22:52,736 --> 00:22:55,102
Write a bill, Britney.
I don't have a car!

433
00:23:01,077 --> 00:23:02,476
Snap Cup time

434
00:23:02,545 --> 00:23:04,843
Gather ye round

435
00:23:04,914 --> 00:23:07,712
Friends and foes together

436
00:23:07,784 --> 00:23:10,218
United and bound

437
00:23:10,286 --> 00:23:12,618
Pass it to your neighbor

438
00:23:12,689 --> 00:23:14,816
Instead of blowing up

439
00:23:14,891 --> 00:23:17,121
And we'll find
harmony and love

440
00:23:17,193 --> 00:23:19,457
In the Snap Cup!

441
00:23:20,964 --> 00:23:23,398
Don't tell me you don't know
what a Snap Cup is?

442
00:23:25,301 --> 00:23:27,235
OK, I'll explain it.

443
00:23:27,303 --> 00:23:30,534
You are going to write down
an anonymous praise note...

444
00:23:30,607 --> 00:23:32,541
on a little warm fuzzy.

445
00:23:32,609 --> 00:23:33,769
Warm fuzzy?

446
00:23:33,843 --> 00:23:35,276
Yes. Compliments
about your co-workers.

447
00:23:35,345 --> 00:23:36,607
Just something nice.

448
00:23:36,679 --> 00:23:40,046
Then you deposit them
in the sacred vessel.

449
00:23:40,116 --> 00:23:43,574
The Snap Cup is essential to
any bipartisan environment.

450
00:23:43,653 --> 00:23:45,518
Consider 1998 Spring Carnival.

451
00:23:45,588 --> 00:23:48,614
The Delta Nus partnered
with the Kappa Kappa Gammas...

452
00:23:48,691 --> 00:23:51,558
on Project Kissing Booth.
Big problems.

453
00:23:51,628 --> 00:23:52,822
Go ahead, write.

454
00:23:52,896 --> 00:23:55,126
So, a whole heated
debate transpired...

455
00:23:55,198 --> 00:23:57,257
over the whole
tongue-no tongue policy.

456
00:23:57,333 --> 00:23:59,164
I think you know what side
the Kappas were on.

457
00:23:59,235 --> 00:24:02,170
Anyway, it really helped us
move past the conflict...

458
00:24:02,238 --> 00:24:03,728
and I think
it can help us today.

459
00:24:03,807 --> 00:24:07,174
Let's just try this, OK?

460
00:24:07,243 --> 00:24:09,575
Thank you, Reena. Thank you.

461
00:24:09,646 --> 00:24:10,840
Thanks for that.

462
00:24:10,914 --> 00:24:13,007
Thank you, Timothy.

463
00:24:14,384 --> 00:24:20,653
So now, the Snap Cup
mistress--me--recites.

464
00:24:21,691 --> 00:24:23,488
Good, I got mine.

465
00:24:24,828 --> 00:24:28,127
"Grace always has the confidence
to speak her mind.

466
00:24:28,198 --> 00:24:31,258
"Plus, she looks terrific
in charcoal."

467
00:24:31,334 --> 00:24:33,734
And, voilà, snaps for Grace!

468
00:24:33,803 --> 00:24:36,772
You see? Our first Snap Cup!

469
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:40,742
This is so exciting!
I wonder what'll happen next?

470
00:24:40,810 --> 00:24:43,779
All right, this is...

471
00:24:43,847 --> 00:24:48,307
"What do Elle Woods and
the Snap Cup have in common?"

472
00:24:48,384 --> 00:24:50,614
A riddle. That's so cool.

473
00:24:50,687 --> 00:24:52,211
I love riddles.

474
00:24:52,288 --> 00:24:55,121
"They're both..."

475
00:24:58,361 --> 00:25:00,420
"stupid."

476
00:25:00,496 --> 00:25:02,225
Enough already.

477
00:25:02,298 --> 00:25:05,096
Maybe we can do something
actually worthwhile...

478
00:25:05,168 --> 00:25:06,601
like attend the hearing
of the committee...

479
00:25:06,669 --> 00:25:08,933
you need to crack.
I'll take you myself.

480
00:25:09,005 --> 00:25:12,964
Thank you, Grace.
That's very generous of you.

481
00:25:13,042 --> 00:25:16,412
See, I think
the Snap Cup really works.

482
00:25:19,549 --> 00:25:20,709
Wow.

483
00:25:20,783 --> 00:25:23,047
Good morning.

484
00:25:23,119 --> 00:25:26,213
This is just like on C-SPAN
except I'm not bored.

485
00:25:26,289 --> 00:25:27,620
You're in the wrong room,
sweetheart.

486
00:25:27,690 --> 00:25:29,590
Intern orientation
is in room...

487
00:25:29,659 --> 00:25:32,856
216? Yes, I've heard.
Thank you.

488
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:40,563
Hi, I'm Elle Woods.
I'm not an intern.

489
00:25:40,637 --> 00:25:42,127
Rob Cole. Me, neither.

490
00:25:42,205 --> 00:25:44,730
I'm the new legislative aide
to Congresswoman Rudd.

491
00:25:44,807 --> 00:25:46,832
I'm an old congressman
from Delaware.

492
00:25:46,910 --> 00:25:50,402
I've been to Delaware!
No sales tax. Good one, sir.

493
00:25:51,447 --> 00:25:53,847
Committee is called to order.

494
00:25:55,785 --> 00:25:59,744
Welcome to
the special meeting of the...

495
00:25:59,822 --> 00:26:01,289
Excuse me. Sorry.

496
00:26:01,357 --> 00:26:04,019
Committee
of Energy and Commerce.

497
00:26:04,093 --> 00:26:07,927
Before we turn
to our official agenda...

498
00:26:07,997 --> 00:26:10,090
are there
any introductory remarks?

499
00:26:10,166 --> 00:26:11,827
Madam chairwoman...

500
00:26:11,901 --> 00:26:13,732
Grace Rossiter,
chief of staff...

501
00:26:13,803 --> 00:26:15,600
Representative Rudd,
Massachusetts.

502
00:26:15,672 --> 00:26:17,435
As our newest
legislative assistant...

503
00:26:17,507 --> 00:26:21,170
will be spearheading a campaign
under your committee...

504
00:26:21,244 --> 00:26:22,973
I'm sure she'd love the floor.

505
00:26:23,046 --> 00:26:27,312
Thus I yield to my colleague,
the lady in hot pink.

506
00:26:27,383 --> 00:26:29,977
You have the floor,
lady in hot pink.

507
00:26:30,053 --> 00:26:31,520
Me?

508
00:26:31,587 --> 00:26:35,455
Would you care to more
specifically identify yourself?

509
00:26:35,525 --> 00:26:37,117
Oh, sure!

510
00:26:37,193 --> 00:26:40,390
My name is Elle Woods,
Boston by way of Bel Air.

511
00:26:40,463 --> 00:26:42,226
And as my surname
would suggest...

512
00:26:42,298 --> 00:26:44,926
I am a passionate advocate
for everything in nature...

513
00:26:45,001 --> 00:26:46,161
and a contented citizen...

514
00:26:46,235 --> 00:26:48,795
until my shorthaired
Chihuahua, Bruiser...

515
00:26:48,871 --> 00:26:52,068
brought me face-to-face with
the animal testing issue.

516
00:26:52,141 --> 00:26:53,540
You're out of order,
Miss Woods.

517
00:26:53,609 --> 00:26:55,839
This is
a fuel efficiency hearing.

518
00:26:55,912 --> 00:26:58,574
I don't see anything in
the agenda about animal testing.

519
00:26:58,648 --> 00:26:59,774
Will you yield the floor?

520
00:26:59,849 --> 00:27:01,373
Absolutely. I'm almost done.

521
00:27:01,451 --> 00:27:03,976
So, in conclusion,
I just want to say...

522
00:27:04,053 --> 00:27:05,384
that I am so excited
about the day...

523
00:27:05,455 --> 00:27:07,582
that I get to march up
those grand Capitol steps...

524
00:27:07,657 --> 00:27:11,320
and drop
that very bill in the...

525
00:27:11,394 --> 00:27:13,021
What's it called?

526
00:27:13,096 --> 00:27:16,065
It's like a shiny,
mahogany box thing?

527
00:27:16,132 --> 00:27:17,258
The hopper.

528
00:27:17,333 --> 00:27:20,200
Exactly! The hopper!
How could I forget?

529
00:27:20,269 --> 00:27:22,635
It's like a bunny.
Perfect for animal testing.

530
00:27:22,705 --> 00:27:24,605
And I want
to let everybody know...

531
00:27:24,674 --> 00:27:27,006
that I'm having
a post-hopper tapas party.

532
00:27:27,076 --> 00:27:30,136
I'm making sangria.
It's really yummy.

533
00:27:30,213 --> 00:27:33,341
My, my, how very interesting
that all sounds.

534
00:27:33,416 --> 00:27:35,577
It'll be fun.

535
00:27:35,651 --> 00:27:37,380
However, the next time
you consider...

536
00:27:37,453 --> 00:27:42,220
attending a hearing
over which I preside... don't!

537
00:27:45,728 --> 00:27:47,389
Committee is called to order.

538
00:27:47,463 --> 00:27:48,725
OK.

539
00:27:48,798 --> 00:27:50,891
Welcome to the special meeting
of the Committee...

540
00:27:50,967 --> 00:27:53,731
of Energy and Commerce.
For the record...

541
00:27:53,803 --> 00:27:55,634
would the secretary
please make note that...

542
00:27:57,206 --> 00:27:59,231
Welcome to the Wellington,
ma'am.

543
00:28:05,548 --> 00:28:07,812
Seventeen-B?

544
00:28:09,986 --> 00:28:12,454
You have a package.

545
00:28:14,190 --> 00:28:17,717
Inside that box are the most
perfect wedding shoes ever.

546
00:28:17,794 --> 00:28:19,421
Both visually stunning
and cleated.

547
00:28:19,495 --> 00:28:20,757
And I won't be able
to wear them...

548
00:28:20,830 --> 00:28:22,593
since I obviously
won't make the date...

549
00:28:22,665 --> 00:28:24,223
for Emmett's fantasy
baseball wedding...

550
00:28:24,300 --> 00:28:25,699
given that I don't have
a chance of getting...

551
00:28:25,768 --> 00:28:28,100
those important congresspeople
to co-sponsor my bill...

552
00:28:28,171 --> 00:28:31,402
which I need to get a hearing
to stop animal testing...

553
00:28:31,474 --> 00:28:32,998
in order to reunite Bruiser
with his mother...

554
00:28:33,076 --> 00:28:34,703
in order to have them
at my wedding...

555
00:28:34,777 --> 00:28:35,937
in which
I was going to wear...

556
00:28:36,012 --> 00:28:38,606
the most perfect
wedding shoes ever...

557
00:28:38,681 --> 00:28:41,149
right inside that box.

558
00:28:41,217 --> 00:28:45,244
They never covered this
in the handbook.

559
00:28:50,259 --> 00:28:53,524
They're something, all right.

560
00:28:55,331 --> 00:28:56,662
You think?

561
00:28:57,900 --> 00:28:59,527
Oh, I'm sorry.

562
00:29:02,738 --> 00:29:05,036
Elle Woods,
legislative aide...

563
00:29:05,108 --> 00:29:07,633
to Congresswoman Rudd,
Massachusetts.

564
00:29:07,710 --> 00:29:10,702
Sid Post. Doorman.

565
00:29:10,780 --> 00:29:13,681
That door.

566
00:29:13,749 --> 00:29:16,877
All day I've felt like white,
open-toed shoes after Labor Day.

567
00:29:16,953 --> 00:29:19,114
I hate that feeling.

568
00:29:19,188 --> 00:29:22,089
Whatever that means.

569
00:29:22,158 --> 00:29:26,754
I better get going.
If I'm going to pass a law...

570
00:29:26,829 --> 00:29:28,990
I have to work up
some plan of attack...

571
00:29:29,065 --> 00:29:33,525
with the Committee
of En and Ron or whatever.

572
00:29:33,603 --> 00:29:35,662
Bye, Sid.

573
00:29:35,738 --> 00:29:39,367
- Comm.
- What'd you say?

574
00:29:39,442 --> 00:29:43,208
It's called the Committee
of Energy and Commerce.

575
00:29:43,279 --> 00:29:47,306
Oh, yeah. Right. Thanks.

576
00:29:56,692 --> 00:29:58,523
This is really
important to me, Grace.

577
00:29:58,594 --> 00:30:00,391
They wouldn't cover
my nana's anti-itch cream...

578
00:30:00,463 --> 00:30:03,159
which means she only has
one free hand for bingo.

579
00:30:03,232 --> 00:30:06,065
- Lf I could get a hearing--
- Where's your bill, Reena?

580
00:30:06,135 --> 00:30:08,365
The staff lawyers couldn't
draft it for six weeks...

581
00:30:08,437 --> 00:30:10,302
but if you could talk to
the congressman's aide...

582
00:30:10,373 --> 00:30:12,136
I could get on the agenda.

583
00:30:12,208 --> 00:30:14,438
We pushed
prescription drugs last term.

584
00:30:14,510 --> 00:30:17,536
I have a lot of issues
that come first.

585
00:30:17,613 --> 00:30:21,777
Reena, if Grace finds herself
otherwise prioritized...

586
00:30:21,851 --> 00:30:23,910
maybe you could talk
to this aide yourself.

587
00:30:23,986 --> 00:30:26,580
Or better yet,
directly to the congressman.

588
00:30:26,656 --> 00:30:30,717
Don't you have something
to alphabetize?

589
00:30:30,793 --> 00:30:34,160
In fact,
now that I think about it...

590
00:30:34,230 --> 00:30:36,562
with Reena's clear passion
for the project...

591
00:30:36,632 --> 00:30:38,293
who better to
write this bill than Reena?

592
00:30:38,367 --> 00:30:39,732
Me?

593
00:30:39,802 --> 00:30:41,167
It's like I always say--

594
00:30:41,237 --> 00:30:43,933
Why let someone else do for you
what you can do for yourself?

595
00:30:44,006 --> 00:30:45,803
Except in the case
of eyebrow maintenance.

596
00:30:45,875 --> 00:30:47,934
We always say follow protocol.

597
00:30:48,010 --> 00:30:49,409
It's worked
for the past 200 years...

598
00:30:49,478 --> 00:30:51,446
OK, Miss Snap Cup?

599
00:30:51,514 --> 00:30:55,780
Stick it out with the lawyers.
They'll get to you eventually.

600
00:30:55,851 --> 00:30:58,786
This is the new
congressmember roster.

601
00:31:04,694 --> 00:31:05,956
Just a dollar.

602
00:31:06,028 --> 00:31:07,825
Don't you believe
in helping a guy out?

603
00:31:07,897 --> 00:31:09,159
What I do believe in, sir...

604
00:31:09,232 --> 00:31:11,325
is an honest day's work
for an honest day's pay.

605
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:12,924
Not rewards for idleness.

606
00:31:13,002 --> 00:31:14,594
- 50 cents?
- Leave me!

607
00:31:14,670 --> 00:31:16,695
- Just a quarter.
- Go bother someone else!

608
00:31:21,143 --> 00:31:23,941
People here
have no common courtesy.

609
00:31:24,013 --> 00:31:26,504
Want to get a hearing
for your bill?

610
00:31:26,582 --> 00:31:29,608
Get Congresswoman Hauser.
She needs a political makeover.

611
00:31:29,685 --> 00:31:32,119
Sidney?

612
00:31:32,188 --> 00:31:34,520
Who needs a what?

613
00:31:34,590 --> 00:31:38,686
Hauser.
Tough redhead on En and Comm.

614
00:31:38,761 --> 00:31:42,026
If she can put her name
on something warm and fuzzy...

615
00:31:42,098 --> 00:31:47,331
something like puppies,
that could do the trick.

616
00:31:47,403 --> 00:31:50,395
Really? What if I showed
Hauser the photos...

617
00:31:50,473 --> 00:31:52,031
of what they're doing
to these animals?

618
00:31:52,108 --> 00:31:57,171
That'd work...
with someone with a heart.

619
00:31:57,246 --> 00:32:00,613
Hauser responds to facts,
figures, and demographics.

620
00:32:00,683 --> 00:32:02,708
You gotta do your homework.

621
00:32:02,785 --> 00:32:05,049
How did you learn all this?

622
00:32:05,121 --> 00:32:06,918
I have been stationed
on the forefront...

623
00:32:06,989 --> 00:32:09,583
of all major political
and social scandals...

624
00:32:09,659 --> 00:32:11,718
for the past 30 years.

625
00:32:11,794 --> 00:32:13,853
You worked in the White House?

626
00:32:13,929 --> 00:32:16,796
No, at the Wellington.

627
00:32:16,866 --> 00:32:19,232
After Hauser,
you'll need Stanford Marks...

628
00:32:19,302 --> 00:32:21,634
Alabama Republican.
A real hard-ass.

629
00:32:21,704 --> 00:32:23,069
Sidney, you are,
without a doubt...

630
00:32:23,139 --> 00:32:26,108
the most useful person
I've met in Washington.

631
00:33:04,513 --> 00:33:06,208
Hauser's margin
in the last election?

632
00:33:06,282 --> 00:33:07,579
Four points. 52-48.

633
00:33:07,650 --> 00:33:08,776
Hauser's chief?

634
00:33:08,851 --> 00:33:11,581
Hall, Ted.
34, moderate, tough.

635
00:33:11,654 --> 00:33:14,521
- Marks' aide?
- Murphy. Conservative, tougher.

636
00:33:14,590 --> 00:33:17,650
- I think you're ready.
- Thank you, Sid.

637
00:33:19,028 --> 00:33:21,861
For shizzle... my ezzle.

638
00:33:27,036 --> 00:33:29,436
I borrowed this.

639
00:33:36,412 --> 00:33:38,312
Excuse me!

640
00:33:38,381 --> 00:33:39,973
Given the historical
tendencies...

641
00:33:40,049 --> 00:33:41,414
of the congresswoman's
voting pool...

642
00:33:41,484 --> 00:33:44,351
animal testing is the very issue
your platform needs.

643
00:33:44,420 --> 00:33:46,513
Which brings me to my
demographic breakdown target.

644
00:33:46,589 --> 00:33:49,649
Which brings us to the end
of our time, but good stuff.

645
00:33:49,725 --> 00:33:50,953
I'll bat it around
with my colleagues.

646
00:33:51,026 --> 00:33:52,721
I'm not done
with my presentation.

647
00:33:52,795 --> 00:33:54,262
- Is Friday good?
- Absolutely.

648
00:33:54,330 --> 00:33:58,266
The second one in November,
and the line starts down there.

649
00:33:58,334 --> 00:34:01,201
But wait!
I won't be here in November.

650
00:34:01,270 --> 00:34:02,703
I'm getting married.

651
00:34:03,939 --> 00:34:05,668
If you insist Congressman Marks
is unavailable...

652
00:34:05,741 --> 00:34:06,867
perhaps you could look at...

653
00:34:06,942 --> 00:34:09,308
my alternative testing
economics incentive chart.

654
00:34:11,580 --> 00:34:13,138
But it's pop-up.

655
00:34:14,717 --> 00:34:18,118
I will read this homeowners
legislation this weekend.

656
00:34:18,187 --> 00:34:20,485
Five more minutes and
I'm due in committee. Reena.

657
00:34:20,556 --> 00:34:21,716
Well--

658
00:34:21,791 --> 00:34:24,021
Reena's prescription drugs
for the elderly amendment--

659
00:34:24,093 --> 00:34:25,583
rejected during mark-up session.

660
00:34:25,661 --> 00:34:26,958
Sorry, Nana.

661
00:34:27,029 --> 00:34:30,430
- Where are we with the animals?
- Still not on the calendar.

662
00:34:30,499 --> 00:34:32,967
So we're nowhere.
Grace, help Elle with this.

663
00:34:33,035 --> 00:34:36,266
Let's get going.
I'll see you all later.

664
00:34:36,338 --> 00:34:38,738
Grace...

665
00:34:38,808 --> 00:34:41,276
I think I can get a meeting
with Hauser's aide.

666
00:34:41,343 --> 00:34:43,538
Please.
You could have 100 meetings...

667
00:34:43,612 --> 00:34:45,045
and it still wouldn't matter.

668
00:34:45,114 --> 00:34:46,843
This is Washington politics...

669
00:34:46,916 --> 00:34:49,282
not warm fuzzies
and kissing booths.

670
00:34:49,351 --> 00:34:51,683
It takes savvy
and street smarts.

671
00:34:51,754 --> 00:34:54,985
I've seen thousands of
polite, idealistic girls...

672
00:34:55,057 --> 00:34:57,924
just like you traipse
up and down this Hill...

673
00:34:57,993 --> 00:35:01,861
and go home empty-handed
with blisters on their feet.

674
00:35:01,931 --> 00:35:05,332
Thank you, Grace.

675
00:35:05,401 --> 00:35:08,734
You actually reminded me
of something really important.

676
00:35:08,804 --> 00:35:11,272
I came here
to give my dog a voice...

677
00:35:11,340 --> 00:35:13,672
and I'd forgotten about my own.

678
00:35:13,742 --> 00:35:16,836
So you can do it
the Washington way.

679
00:35:16,912 --> 00:35:21,474
But I'm going to do it
the Elle Woods way.

680
00:35:21,550 --> 00:35:21,650
Time to get serious.

681
00:35:21,650 --> 00:35:23,083
Time to get serious.

682
00:35:23,152 --> 00:35:25,780
Subject--Congresswoman
Libby Hauser.

683
00:35:25,855 --> 00:35:27,254
Came of age in Post-War boom...

684
00:35:27,323 --> 00:35:30,724
typified by 1951
Charles Jourdan stiletto heel.

685
00:35:30,793 --> 00:35:33,523
Moving up to the Texan's head,
which is red...

686
00:35:33,596 --> 00:35:36,429
suspect chemical assistance.
Must pursue.

687
00:35:36,499 --> 00:35:38,057
Hit me, Post.

688
00:35:38,133 --> 00:35:40,693
118 salons within
a 10-mile radius...

689
00:35:40,769 --> 00:35:42,930
broken down
by color expertise...

690
00:35:43,005 --> 00:35:48,375
and philosophical approach
to hair maintenance and style.

691
00:35:48,444 --> 00:35:51,413
I didn't know you could have
a philosophy of hair.

692
00:35:51,480 --> 00:35:52,777
Oh, yeah.

693
00:35:52,848 --> 00:35:55,146
Maybe that's where I went wrong.

694
00:35:56,719 --> 00:35:57,913
Go for Woods.

695
00:35:57,987 --> 00:35:59,750
It's just as you suspected.

696
00:35:59,822 --> 00:36:01,949
She's at a moderate
conservative salon...

697
00:36:02,024 --> 00:36:04,458
founded on
the principles of Vidal.

698
00:36:04,527 --> 00:36:07,519
In fact, it was one
of our case studies...

699
00:36:07,596 --> 00:36:09,757
last year at Hair University.

700
00:36:09,832 --> 00:36:12,062
That was right
before they flunked me.

701
00:36:12,134 --> 00:36:14,432
Paulette, they weren't ready
for your vision.

702
00:36:14,503 --> 00:36:17,131
I know you'll make
your mark hair-wise.

703
00:36:18,307 --> 00:36:19,774
Sorry.

704
00:36:19,842 --> 00:36:22,208
- You got a pen?
- Yes.

705
00:36:22,278 --> 00:36:24,473
It's at Constitution and 12th.

706
00:36:24,547 --> 00:36:27,107
The Salon Bontempo.

707
00:36:30,486 --> 00:36:32,647
Don't you just love a salon day?

708
00:36:35,558 --> 00:36:39,119
Yes, so peaceful and quiet.

709
00:36:39,194 --> 00:36:41,492
Makes it so much easier
to talk that way.

710
00:36:41,564 --> 00:36:43,122
They have rules about that here.

711
00:36:43,198 --> 00:36:45,826
I know. That's why
I called to make sure...

712
00:36:45,901 --> 00:36:47,766
they used PETA-approved
hair care products.

713
00:36:47,836 --> 00:36:49,997
When you think about what
they do to those animals--

714
00:36:50,072 --> 00:36:52,131
Which is why
I don't think about it.

715
00:36:52,207 --> 00:36:53,834
Does the trick.

716
00:36:57,780 --> 00:36:59,145
Excellent bobby pin handling.

717
00:36:59,214 --> 00:37:02,206
Thank you, Frederic.
Looks great.

718
00:37:04,653 --> 00:37:06,450
Isn't it
so comforting to see...

719
00:37:06,522 --> 00:37:08,513
they use eco-friendly
foil technology here?

720
00:37:08,591 --> 00:37:11,185
Every planet needs a friend,
that's what I always say.

721
00:37:11,260 --> 00:37:14,093
If I wanted to talk about
the emotional life of a rock...

722
00:37:14,163 --> 00:37:16,996
you'd know it by now.

723
00:37:17,066 --> 00:37:19,500
Until this day,
I'd held the highest opinion...

724
00:37:19,568 --> 00:37:22,264
of redheads as a fellow
hair minority group.

725
00:37:22,338 --> 00:37:24,499
I heard quite enough
of your politics...

726
00:37:24,573 --> 00:37:26,700
at the committee meeting,
thank you very much.

727
00:37:44,226 --> 00:37:47,684
When was the last time you wore
the yellow tea rose?

728
00:37:55,170 --> 00:37:57,434
I'm sorry?
What did you just--

729
00:37:57,506 --> 00:37:59,940
When was the last time
you wore your yellow tea rose?

730
00:38:00,009 --> 00:38:02,239
On the night of my initiation.

731
00:38:02,311 --> 00:38:04,506
Wasn't the passing of the secret
scented eternal flame...

732
00:38:04,580 --> 00:38:07,174
of the goddess Delta Nu
not the most moving experience?

733
00:38:07,249 --> 00:38:09,274
Especially the part
where we sipped...

734
00:38:09,351 --> 00:38:12,013
from the secret
pink chalice of sisterhood!

735
00:38:12,087 --> 00:38:13,816
Yes!

736
00:38:18,193 --> 00:38:20,354
Delta who?

737
00:38:20,429 --> 00:38:22,590
Delta Nu!

738
00:38:22,665 --> 00:38:25,896
Delta-Delta boo-gah-loo

739
00:38:25,968 --> 00:38:28,596
Nu Nu Delta

740
00:38:28,671 --> 00:38:30,002
Theta, Beta

741
00:38:30,072 --> 00:38:31,471
Lambda, Mu

742
00:38:31,540 --> 00:38:35,135
Ooh-aah, Delta Nu!

743
00:38:36,679 --> 00:38:39,842
Libby Hauser, Texas.
Planning a wedding?

744
00:38:39,915 --> 00:38:42,816
That "I do" updo
looks like heaven on you.

745
00:38:42,885 --> 00:38:44,045
Thank you.

746
00:38:44,119 --> 00:38:46,644
Who is he?
Zeta Lambda Nu, I hope.

747
00:38:46,722 --> 00:38:48,815
Actually, I'm marrying
outside the Greek system...

748
00:38:48,891 --> 00:38:50,620
but he's totally letter-worthy.

749
00:38:50,693 --> 00:38:55,130
But how is D.C. Elle-worthy?

750
00:38:55,197 --> 00:38:57,722
I'm here to speak for those
who can't speak for themselves.

751
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:59,768
How interesting.

752
00:38:59,835 --> 00:39:02,133
It's more than interesting.
It's practical.

753
00:39:02,204 --> 00:39:04,570
Strictly a numbers game
as far as you're concerned.

754
00:39:04,640 --> 00:39:10,237
125,468--Number of people in
your district with dog licenses.

755
00:39:10,312 --> 00:39:14,248
12,762--The number of
unemployed scientists...

756
00:39:14,316 --> 00:39:17,251
with the skills to develop
alternatives to animal testing.

757
00:39:17,319 --> 00:39:21,983
And finally, 6285--the ID number
of my dog's captive mother.

758
00:39:22,057 --> 00:39:25,185
I'm not sure
I followed all that...

759
00:39:25,260 --> 00:39:26,750
but you got my attention.

760
00:39:26,829 --> 00:39:28,421
If there's one thing
I know how to do...

761
00:39:28,497 --> 00:39:30,590
it's rinse and repeat.
Shall we?

762
00:39:32,568 --> 00:39:33,728
Excuse me,
do you happen to have a--

763
00:39:33,802 --> 00:39:35,793
- Get lost!
- Excuse me, sir!

764
00:39:35,871 --> 00:39:39,204
- Do you have a--
- No, I'm busy.

765
00:39:39,274 --> 00:39:41,208
Sir, could I use a section
of your newspaper?

766
00:39:41,276 --> 00:39:43,335
We're late for
your doggie spa appointment.

767
00:39:48,016 --> 00:39:50,507
- Here you go.
- Thank you, young lady.

768
00:39:50,586 --> 00:39:52,645
No problem. What kind
of world would this be...

769
00:39:52,721 --> 00:39:55,189
if we didn't help each other out
every once in a while?

770
00:39:55,257 --> 00:39:57,725
Have a good day.

771
00:39:57,793 --> 00:39:59,454
What do you want, Bruiser?

772
00:40:05,300 --> 00:40:06,665
Bruiser, honey, come on.

773
00:40:15,377 --> 00:40:16,571
We have to go. We're late.

774
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:20,573
We have to get to
the doggie spa, remember?

775
00:40:20,649 --> 00:40:24,085
Will it be Swedish
or shiatsu massage today?

776
00:40:24,153 --> 00:40:26,121
Come on.

777
00:40:29,858 --> 00:40:32,349
Come on. We gotta get you
to the puppy pretty parlor.

778
00:40:33,996 --> 00:40:36,521
Redhead, down.

779
00:40:36,598 --> 00:40:38,657
Up next is Stanford Marks...

780
00:40:38,734 --> 00:40:41,328
Southern conservative,
NRA spokesman.

781
00:40:41,403 --> 00:40:43,462
How about tulips?

782
00:40:43,539 --> 00:40:47,305
No, no, the calla lily
is this year's tulip.

783
00:40:47,376 --> 00:40:50,243
- For weddings?
- It's all about the calla.

784
00:40:50,312 --> 00:40:52,337
What would I do without you?

785
00:40:52,414 --> 00:40:54,780
I couldn't do anything
without you, Sid.

786
00:40:55,884 --> 00:40:57,579
You're going to get
this bill through, Elle.

787
00:40:57,653 --> 00:41:01,749
An honest voice
is louder than a crowd's.

788
00:41:01,824 --> 00:41:03,883
Just trust your voice.

789
00:41:07,863 --> 00:41:12,630
Bruiser? Oh, my God.
I'll be right back.

790
00:41:12,701 --> 00:41:12,835
Pilates for Poodles?
That's Tuesday at 2:30.

791
00:41:12,835 --> 00:41:15,702
Pilates for Poodles?
That's Tuesday at 2:30.

792
00:41:17,539 --> 00:41:19,063
- The page said it was urgent!
- They said it was urgent.

793
00:41:19,141 --> 00:41:21,006
- Please tell me he's OK.
- What's wrong with Leslie?

794
00:41:21,076 --> 00:41:22,873
We have it under control now...

795
00:41:22,945 --> 00:41:24,913
but your Rottweiler
has been humping...

796
00:41:24,980 --> 00:41:27,710
your little dog,
and vice versa.

797
00:41:27,783 --> 00:41:30,445
Your Chihuahua's quite
the little leaper, young lady.

798
00:41:30,519 --> 00:41:32,487
Takes a running start.

799
00:41:32,554 --> 00:41:35,921
Hell, what can I say?
My Rottweiler's a stallion.

800
00:41:35,991 --> 00:41:39,154
In our household, we fully
support a healthy curiosity.

801
00:41:39,228 --> 00:41:43,995
Testosterone is natural.
Wait. Did you say stallion?

802
00:41:44,066 --> 00:41:46,057
Wait a minute. Your dog...

803
00:41:46,134 --> 00:41:48,227
the one wearing that ridiculous
pink skirt in the park?

804
00:41:48,303 --> 00:41:50,396
Why would she have testosterone?

805
00:41:50,472 --> 00:41:52,167
That wasn't a skirt,
it was a skort.

806
00:41:52,241 --> 00:41:54,038
- Men wear skorts.
- Uh-huh.

807
00:41:54,109 --> 00:41:55,804
What the heck is a skort?

808
00:41:55,878 --> 00:41:57,812
And what does a man wearing one
got to do with it?

809
00:41:57,880 --> 00:42:04,513
All right! Leslie is a Les.
The Rottweiler is a guy...

810
00:42:04,586 --> 00:42:10,024
and Bruiser is a male dog
who enjoys wearing pastel.

811
00:42:10,092 --> 00:42:13,220
The canines are both male.

812
00:42:18,634 --> 00:42:22,035
Your dogs are gay.

813
00:42:32,180 --> 00:42:35,513
All the signs were there.
I just didn't see them.

814
00:42:35,584 --> 00:42:37,814
Most dogs
like to chew your shoes...

815
00:42:37,886 --> 00:42:41,287
and Bruiser liked to wear mine.

816
00:42:41,356 --> 00:42:44,587
I just thought
he liked the height.

817
00:42:44,660 --> 00:42:45,888
You just want
what's best for them.

818
00:42:45,961 --> 00:42:47,394
Doesn't matter
if they're the smartest...

819
00:42:47,462 --> 00:42:50,260
or the strongest
or the best diggers.

820
00:42:50,332 --> 00:42:53,392
As long as they're happy.

821
00:42:53,468 --> 00:42:56,335
Why me? Why my dog?

822
00:42:56,405 --> 00:42:59,169
I told Doris not
to buy it in Dupont Circle.

823
00:42:59,241 --> 00:43:03,371
That damn homosexual
puppy boutique.

824
00:43:03,445 --> 00:43:06,414
Stanford Marks, by the way.
You can call me Stan.

825
00:43:06,481 --> 00:43:08,278
Elle Woods.
Very nice to meet you.

826
00:43:08,350 --> 00:43:10,716
You're the girl with
the perfumed poo baggies.

827
00:43:10,786 --> 00:43:13,880
I'm the woman with
the scented waste receptacles.

828
00:43:13,956 --> 00:43:17,517
Wait!
Congressman Stanford Marks?

829
00:43:17,592 --> 00:43:18,923
As in the Southern
conservative...

830
00:43:18,994 --> 00:43:21,394
NRA spokesman Alabama
Republican Stanford Marks?

831
00:43:21,463 --> 00:43:22,760
One and the same.

832
00:43:22,831 --> 00:43:24,093
It's a pleasure
to make your acquaintance.

833
00:43:24,166 --> 00:43:27,294
No, Congressman,
the pleasure is all mine.

834
00:43:27,369 --> 00:43:29,929
- Well...
- Believe me.

835
00:43:30,005 --> 00:43:32,940
Here's to getting things
done the Washington way.

836
00:43:33,008 --> 00:43:35,340
Your chief of staff
has just gotten herself...

837
00:43:35,410 --> 00:43:38,675
a meeting with--wait for it--
Chairman Stan Marks...

838
00:43:38,747 --> 00:43:40,738
in just four short weeks.

839
00:43:40,816 --> 00:43:43,683
- Congratulations, Grace.
- Yes!

840
00:43:45,454 --> 00:43:49,049
Oh, yes.
OK, who wants to bet...

841
00:43:49,124 --> 00:43:50,955
over-under
on Ms. Woods departure?

842
00:43:51,026 --> 00:43:52,584
Right now it's at six days.

843
00:43:52,661 --> 00:43:53,328
- Reena?
- No, thanks.

844
00:43:53,328 --> 00:43:54,625
- Reena?
- No, thanks.

845
00:43:54,696 --> 00:43:56,323
Come on. Anybody?

846
00:43:56,398 --> 00:43:57,695
Who wants to take
over six days?

847
00:43:57,766 --> 00:43:59,393
I'll take it, Grace.

848
00:43:59,468 --> 00:44:01,663
I've been so busy.
I'm sorry I'm late.

849
00:44:01,737 --> 00:44:03,728
Reena, could you be a pal
and just tell me...

850
00:44:03,805 --> 00:44:05,796
what I'm doing
a week from tomorrow?

851
00:44:05,874 --> 00:44:08,069
By the way, that outfit
looks fantastic on you.

852
00:44:08,143 --> 00:44:09,974
It really brings out
the color in your eyes.

853
00:44:10,045 --> 00:44:11,979
Thanks.

854
00:44:12,047 --> 00:44:14,675
It's on my "I brake for
sample sales" bookmark.

855
00:44:16,618 --> 00:44:20,179
9:00--sample custom color
wedding cake frosting.

856
00:44:20,255 --> 00:44:22,382
10:00--
rehearse hearing speech.

857
00:44:22,457 --> 00:44:24,152
11:00--
Commerce committee hearing.

858
00:44:24,226 --> 00:44:26,456
12:00--
exfoliating treatment--

859
00:44:26,528 --> 00:44:29,292
Go back to that one at 11:00.

860
00:44:29,364 --> 00:44:32,822
11:00--
Commerce committee hearing.

861
00:44:32,901 --> 00:44:34,300
That's what it says.

862
00:44:34,369 --> 00:44:35,996
I'm going to be appearing
before ranking member...

863
00:44:36,071 --> 00:44:37,663
Libby Hauser,
Chairman Stanford Marks...

864
00:44:37,739 --> 00:44:39,366
and the entire Committee
of En and Comm.

865
00:44:39,441 --> 00:44:42,171
A hop, skip, and a jump
away from a floor vote.

866
00:44:42,244 --> 00:44:43,836
Nice try, but you
have to get a bill...

867
00:44:43,912 --> 00:44:45,311
before you have a hearing.

868
00:44:45,380 --> 00:44:47,007
Like this one?

869
00:44:47,082 --> 00:44:49,107
It's like I was saying
to the congresswoman...

870
00:44:49,184 --> 00:44:50,981
the other day over
caramel macchiatos.

871
00:44:51,053 --> 00:44:53,317
"Is bill writing
super fun or what?"

872
00:44:53,388 --> 00:44:55,185
I think so.

873
00:44:55,257 --> 00:44:58,454
Where is that Elle Woods?

874
00:44:58,527 --> 00:45:01,496
Oh, my God.

875
00:45:01,563 --> 00:45:04,532
- Libby just told me the news.
- She did?

876
00:45:04,599 --> 00:45:05,930
Never underestimate a woman...

877
00:45:06,001 --> 00:45:07,866
with a French manicure
and a Harvard law degree.

878
00:45:07,936 --> 00:45:09,904
Thank you, Victoria.
That's very sweet of you...

879
00:45:09,971 --> 00:45:12,906
but I couldn't have done it
without your inspiration.

880
00:45:12,974 --> 00:45:15,772
I'm honored.
This girl is special.

881
00:45:15,844 --> 00:45:18,608
Actually, I didn't do it alone.

882
00:45:18,680 --> 00:45:21,979
The entire team helped me.
It was really a group effort.

883
00:45:22,050 --> 00:45:24,575
Good work, guys.
Really good work.

884
00:45:24,653 --> 00:45:26,746
- You.
- Thanks.

885
00:45:27,823 --> 00:45:30,383
Thank you, Reena.
You're a sweetheart.

886
00:45:30,459 --> 00:45:33,724
And I guess I will see you
at the hopper.

887
00:46:09,364 --> 00:46:11,298
Ask not what your best friend
can do for man...

888
00:46:11,366 --> 00:46:14,096
but what you can do
for man's best friend.

889
00:46:19,441 --> 00:46:20,738
The Committee
on Energy and Commerce...

890
00:46:20,809 --> 00:46:22,538
will now come to order.

891
00:46:22,611 --> 00:46:26,513
HR 2562,
aka Bruiser's Bill--

892
00:46:26,581 --> 00:46:28,981
Representative
Victoria Rudd, sponsor...

893
00:46:29,050 --> 00:46:30,984
proposing a ban
on animal testing...

894
00:46:31,052 --> 00:46:33,145
in the cosmetics industry.

895
00:46:33,221 --> 00:46:34,654
I'd like to welcome
you all today as we begin...

896
00:46:34,723 --> 00:46:36,850
consideration of
this very important issue.

897
00:46:36,925 --> 00:46:39,723
This week, you will hear
testimony from both sides...

898
00:46:39,794 --> 00:46:44,197
and I ask that you keep
your ears and your minds open.

899
00:46:44,266 --> 00:46:46,234
This is my first
congressional hearing.

900
00:46:46,301 --> 00:46:48,030
Can you believe it?

901
00:46:48,103 --> 00:46:49,468
And so I come to you today
as a citizen...

902
00:46:49,538 --> 00:46:51,870
and a scientist with
the National Institute of Health

903
00:46:51,940 --> 00:46:54,431
for 25 years,
during which time...

904
00:46:54,509 --> 00:46:56,977
it's become increasingly clear
that these supposed alternatives

905
00:46:57,045 --> 00:47:00,276
to animal testing
aren't alternatives at all.

906
00:47:00,348 --> 00:47:04,284
I took this office to represent
my two-legged constituents.

907
00:47:04,352 --> 00:47:08,288
Recently, I saw an item in
a pet store with the label...

908
00:47:08,356 --> 00:47:11,052
"This product
is tested on humans."

909
00:47:11,126 --> 00:47:13,026
That's a problem
worth discussing.

910
00:47:17,432 --> 00:47:18,865
All the bleeding hearts...

911
00:47:18,934 --> 00:47:20,595
will try to distract us
from the facts...

912
00:47:20,669 --> 00:47:23,729
with their saccharine talk
of wagging tails...

913
00:47:23,805 --> 00:47:27,400
cold noses, and other
sentimental mumbo jumbo.

914
00:47:27,475 --> 00:47:30,501
Consider this--where we see
softness of heart...

915
00:47:30,579 --> 00:47:33,207
we often see softness of mind.

916
00:47:33,281 --> 00:47:36,045
And so to move on such a bill
at this juncture in time...

917
00:47:36,117 --> 00:47:38,449
would wreak havoc
on already unstable...

918
00:47:38,520 --> 00:47:41,387
local economies
across the country.

919
00:47:41,456 --> 00:47:44,050
Now, that's a problem
worth discussing.

920
00:47:46,228 --> 00:47:47,889
You know
I'd do anything for you...

921
00:47:47,963 --> 00:47:49,897
but I got to tell you,
that is one tough room.

922
00:47:49,965 --> 00:47:52,126
- Better be prepared tomorrow.
- All right.

923
00:47:52,200 --> 00:47:54,634
Excuse me, ladies.
Good evening.

924
00:47:54,703 --> 00:47:58,195
I know you've had
a bad day in court before.

925
00:47:58,273 --> 00:47:59,501
It's the same thing.

926
00:47:59,574 --> 00:48:01,633
They make their case,
we make ours.

927
00:48:01,710 --> 00:48:03,143
Yes, but that was bad.

928
00:48:03,211 --> 00:48:06,612
They're mostly posturing for
their constituents back home.

929
00:48:06,681 --> 00:48:08,478
I think we have the votes
in committee...

930
00:48:08,550 --> 00:48:10,279
even without your testimony.

931
00:48:10,352 --> 00:48:14,118
But they have scientists
and economists and facts.

932
00:48:14,189 --> 00:48:17,352
So do we.
Elle, listen to me.

933
00:48:17,425 --> 00:48:20,758
Go home.
Have an early evening.

934
00:48:20,829 --> 00:48:22,854
Sorry.

935
00:48:22,931 --> 00:48:25,832
Victoria Rudd. Yes.

936
00:48:25,900 --> 00:48:28,698
Hang on one minute, will you?

937
00:48:28,770 --> 00:48:31,603
Go home. Try to relax.

938
00:48:31,673 --> 00:48:35,541
And don't think like them.
Think like you.

939
00:48:35,610 --> 00:48:37,976
OK. Thanks.

940
00:48:38,046 --> 00:48:40,139
- Good night.
- Good night.

941
00:48:42,384 --> 00:48:43,976
Bob, how are you?

942
00:48:48,089 --> 00:48:50,649
I'm leaving the Capitol
right now.

943
00:48:50,725 --> 00:48:53,660
- Thanks. Nice work.
- Oh.

944
00:48:58,366 --> 00:48:59,492
Sid?

945
00:48:59,567 --> 00:49:03,025
I'm sorry about that.
This happens all the time.

946
00:49:03,104 --> 00:49:04,696
My break is almost up...

947
00:49:04,773 --> 00:49:08,368
but I wanted to get you this
before tomorrow.

948
00:49:08,443 --> 00:49:10,001
Great. Let's walk.

949
00:49:11,546 --> 00:49:13,446
Sidney, this is brilliant.

950
00:49:13,515 --> 00:49:15,574
How did you know all this?

951
00:49:15,650 --> 00:49:19,211
Hundreds of dogs walked and
thousands of plastic baggies.

952
00:49:19,287 --> 00:49:22,120
This is perfect.
This is exactly what I need.

953
00:49:23,525 --> 00:49:26,961
Well, of course
I appreciate your support.

954
00:49:27,028 --> 00:49:28,427
Why wouldn't it continue?

955
00:49:28,496 --> 00:49:31,624
I'm already on record
on that issue.

956
00:49:37,305 --> 00:49:38,897
All right.

957
00:49:38,973 --> 00:49:40,804
I'll do what I can.

958
00:49:40,875 --> 00:49:43,309
Don't push me, Bob.

959
00:49:43,378 --> 00:49:45,243
I'll do what I can.

960
00:49:45,313 --> 00:49:47,645
All right. Good night.

961
00:49:51,986 --> 00:49:55,888
- I need to call in my favor.
- I'm listening.

962
00:49:55,957 --> 00:49:59,393
I've changed my position
on Bruiser's Bill.

963
00:49:59,461 --> 00:50:02,555
A man who controls
a political machine...

964
00:50:02,630 --> 00:50:05,929
Boy, he's good.
He is really good.

965
00:50:06,000 --> 00:50:07,729
I'm really glad
we're watching this.

966
00:50:07,802 --> 00:50:09,463
This is good for you.

967
00:50:09,537 --> 00:50:10,731
He promised to break me in two.

968
00:50:10,805 --> 00:50:12,170
I'm starting
to worry about...

969
00:50:12,240 --> 00:50:14,003
getting all
this wedding planning done.

970
00:50:14,075 --> 00:50:17,476
Elle, I want you to follow
my lead in Washington.

971
00:50:17,545 --> 00:50:20,605
And always make sure
Bruiser wears a sweater.

972
00:50:20,682 --> 00:50:23,981
- Is that Sean Connery?
- No, it's not.

973
00:50:24,052 --> 00:50:25,542
Powerful enough
to control congressmen...

974
00:50:25,620 --> 00:50:28,145
Seriously, honey, don't worry
about the wedding research.

975
00:50:28,223 --> 00:50:30,555
Just give 'em hell tomorrow.

976
00:50:47,108 --> 00:50:50,009
The chair now recognizes
legislative aide Elle Woods.

977
00:50:57,752 --> 00:50:58,878
Thank you, Mr. Chairman.

978
00:50:58,953 --> 00:51:00,614
There she is!

979
00:51:00,688 --> 00:51:03,122
Guys, she really did it.

980
00:51:04,392 --> 00:51:05,654
Miss Woods?

981
00:51:05,727 --> 00:51:07,456
Well, I'll be damned.

982
00:51:07,529 --> 00:51:10,123
Representative Kroft...

983
00:51:10,198 --> 00:51:12,689
that lip gloss looks absolutely
sensational on you.

984
00:51:13,735 --> 00:51:15,225
I'm sorry, what?

985
00:51:15,303 --> 00:51:17,737
It's Raspberry Macaroon
number 156.

986
00:51:17,806 --> 00:51:19,797
Company shall remain nameless,
is that correct?

987
00:51:19,874 --> 00:51:24,368
Well, yes. But how did you--

988
00:51:24,446 --> 00:51:26,141
What if I told you,
Representative Kroft...

989
00:51:26,214 --> 00:51:28,273
that you owe that
special bounce in your step...

990
00:51:28,349 --> 00:51:31,079
that only comes from finding
the perfect lipstick...

991
00:51:31,152 --> 00:51:35,145
to the pain and suffering
of innocent animals?

992
00:51:35,223 --> 00:51:36,656
What if I was to tell you...

993
00:51:36,724 --> 00:51:38,749
Congresswoman
Madeline Melanie Kroft...

994
00:51:38,827 --> 00:51:41,159
that you owe
your Raspberry Macaroon...

995
00:51:43,665 --> 00:51:46,691
to him?

996
00:51:46,768 --> 00:51:48,326
My best friend.

997
00:51:52,841 --> 00:51:54,604
Bruiser.

998
00:51:54,676 --> 00:51:57,702
How many times
has he acted on my behalf?

999
00:51:57,779 --> 00:52:00,043
Countless.

1000
00:52:00,114 --> 00:52:05,450
But today, I get the opportunity
to speak for him.

1001
00:52:05,520 --> 00:52:08,455
Who do you speak for?

1002
00:52:13,795 --> 00:52:15,695
Congressman Fuchs...

1003
00:52:15,763 --> 00:52:19,460
the next time you reach for your
overnight moisturizing gloves--

1004
00:52:19,534 --> 00:52:21,195
By the way, it's nothing
to be ashamed about.

1005
00:52:21,269 --> 00:52:23,396
More men should use them.

1006
00:52:23,471 --> 00:52:27,567
Consider asking yourself what
you're willing to sacrifice...

1007
00:52:27,642 --> 00:52:30,270
in the name of
beauty and soft cuticles.

1008
00:52:30,345 --> 00:52:33,940
Are you willing to sacrifice
animal welfare?

1009
00:52:34,015 --> 00:52:36,677
Or how about
the welfare of one animal?

1010
00:52:36,751 --> 00:52:39,413
Like Jelly,
your childhood pal...

1011
00:52:39,487 --> 00:52:42,650
that striking
retriever-black lab mix.

1012
00:52:44,826 --> 00:52:48,489
You know about Jelly?

1013
00:52:48,563 --> 00:52:51,691
When all the other children
refused to play Lone Ranger...

1014
00:52:51,766 --> 00:52:53,996
who was it that was
always your Tonto?

1015
00:52:54,068 --> 00:52:56,593
Jelly Belly.

1016
00:53:07,715 --> 00:53:10,650
Mr. Chairman...

1017
00:53:10,718 --> 00:53:12,811
when you look in those
snap-worthy almond eyes...

1018
00:53:12,887 --> 00:53:14,115
of your Rottweiler Leslie...

1019
00:53:14,188 --> 00:53:16,952
does it not make your heart
glow with warmth?

1020
00:53:17,025 --> 00:53:20,119
With due respect, Ms. Woods,
I wouldn't go that far.

1021
00:53:20,194 --> 00:53:21,718
But when he learned
to differentiate...

1022
00:53:21,796 --> 00:53:23,593
between seven different
kinds of pipes...

1023
00:53:23,665 --> 00:53:25,997
and fetch each one on command,
did you not swear...

1024
00:53:26,067 --> 00:53:28,194
to protect him
with every shotgun...

1025
00:53:28,269 --> 00:53:32,399
in your charming little
ammunitions case?

1026
00:53:32,473 --> 00:53:33,804
It wouldn't come to that.

1027
00:53:33,875 --> 00:53:37,140
This is a dog
we're talking about.

1028
00:53:37,211 --> 00:53:39,406
But if you could speak
for Leslie...

1029
00:53:39,480 --> 00:53:41,573
what would you say?

1030
00:53:46,220 --> 00:53:51,385
What would Leslie want you
to say for him, Mr. Chairman?

1031
00:53:54,829 --> 00:53:56,797
Stan.

1032
00:54:06,908 --> 00:54:08,068
To hell with it.

1033
00:54:09,444 --> 00:54:12,902
My Rottweiler Les is
of the homosexual orientation.

1034
00:54:13,948 --> 00:54:16,746
I've said it. I'm out.

1035
00:54:16,818 --> 00:54:19,252
My name is Stan Marks,
I'm a conservative Republican...

1036
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:21,379
NRA spokesman,
and my dog is gay.

1037
00:54:21,456 --> 00:54:23,720
And guess what?

1038
00:54:23,791 --> 00:54:26,885
I couldn't be prouder
of the little flamer!

1039
00:54:26,961 --> 00:54:29,259
I don't care
how good my hair looks...

1040
00:54:29,330 --> 00:54:31,525
slicked back with
some high-dollar pomade.

1041
00:54:31,599 --> 00:54:35,433
Just one long stare into
that sweet sissy dog's eyes...

1042
00:54:35,503 --> 00:54:40,566
and I know no cosmetic
could ever be worth it!

1043
00:54:40,642 --> 00:54:45,079
Bruiser's Bill.

1044
00:54:45,146 --> 00:54:46,875
Bruiser's Bill!

1045
00:54:49,617 --> 00:54:51,585
We did it! Bill passing!

1046
00:54:51,653 --> 00:54:54,281
Bruiser's Bill!

1047
00:54:54,355 --> 00:54:56,380
Important legislation
for our time.

1048
00:55:07,168 --> 00:55:09,432
Bruiser, good work, little guy.

1049
00:55:14,709 --> 00:55:16,438
I would like
to conclude this hearing...

1050
00:55:16,511 --> 00:55:18,342
by thanking you all
for your testimony--

1051
00:55:18,413 --> 00:55:19,778
Mr. Chairman, sir...

1052
00:55:19,847 --> 00:55:21,007
The chair recognizes...

1053
00:55:21,082 --> 00:55:22,709
the gentlewoman
from Massachusetts.

1054
00:55:22,784 --> 00:55:25,048
Mr. Chairman,
committee members...

1055
00:55:25,119 --> 00:55:28,646
I would like to thank you for
your consideration of this bill.

1056
00:55:28,723 --> 00:55:31,521
However,
after further reflection...

1057
00:55:31,592 --> 00:55:34,720
on the budgetary realities
of this fiscal year...

1058
00:55:34,796 --> 00:55:38,254
I feel I must withdraw
my support for Bruiser's Bill.

1059
00:55:38,332 --> 00:55:40,994
- What?
- I concur!

1060
00:55:53,314 --> 00:55:55,282
Everybody, calm down.

1061
00:56:04,559 --> 00:56:06,390
I'm sorry, Bruiser.

1062
00:56:08,162 --> 00:56:10,494
I'm sorry, too, Elle.

1063
00:56:10,565 --> 00:56:12,829
I know you think
I've let you down.

1064
00:56:12,900 --> 00:56:15,368
Believe me, I thought
about your reaction...

1065
00:56:15,436 --> 00:56:17,461
maybe more than I should have.

1066
00:56:19,240 --> 00:56:21,936
You were outmaneuvered...

1067
00:56:22,009 --> 00:56:23,874
by Grace.

1068
00:56:23,945 --> 00:56:25,708
Grace?

1069
00:56:25,780 --> 00:56:28,214
For the last two sessions
she's been pushing...

1070
00:56:28,282 --> 00:56:30,409
this homeowners incentives bill.

1071
00:56:30,485 --> 00:56:32,612
This morning she struck a deal.

1072
00:56:32,687 --> 00:56:36,555
I withdraw my support
for Bruiser's Bill.

1073
00:56:36,624 --> 00:56:40,253
Homeowners incentives
comes to a vote.

1074
00:56:40,328 --> 00:56:42,319
That was the price
and I paid it.

1075
00:56:42,396 --> 00:56:46,492
That's all just deals
and trades and secrets.

1076
00:56:50,204 --> 00:56:53,230
That's not what people want.

1077
00:57:01,616 --> 00:57:05,313
Elle... I'm sorry.

1078
00:57:14,095 --> 00:57:16,029
Government of the people...

1079
00:57:16,097 --> 00:57:19,464
by the people, for the people.

1080
00:57:44,458 --> 00:57:47,325
So what's your story?

1081
00:57:47,395 --> 00:57:49,886
Were you even honest?

1082
00:57:51,265 --> 00:57:53,233
I guess you were.

1083
00:57:56,871 --> 00:57:58,099
If you didn't play games...

1084
00:57:58,172 --> 00:58:01,471
then you were probably
the only one.

1085
00:58:04,145 --> 00:58:06,875
I just don't know how
you did it.

1086
00:58:06,948 --> 00:58:09,280
I don't even mean
wearing that silly hat...

1087
00:58:09,350 --> 00:58:11,284
because that was really brave.

1088
00:58:11,352 --> 00:58:13,479
But...

1089
00:58:13,554 --> 00:58:16,489
Just trusting your country.

1090
00:58:16,557 --> 00:58:19,117
Trusting this system...

1091
00:58:22,296 --> 00:58:24,560
Trusting yourself.

1092
00:58:24,632 --> 00:58:26,793
I did.

1093
00:58:41,716 --> 00:58:44,776
Go on.
It's full of warm fuzzies.

1094
00:58:44,852 --> 00:58:47,650
With extra fuzz.

1095
00:58:59,934 --> 00:59:03,062
"Elle Woods has amazing
lateral delts."

1096
00:59:03,137 --> 00:59:06,038
That was my target
muscle group of the month.

1097
00:59:06,107 --> 00:59:08,974
Snaps for Elle's lateral delts.

1098
00:59:24,759 --> 00:59:27,057
"Elle Woods inspires us."

1099
00:59:29,297 --> 00:59:31,094
We even put little hearts
over the "Is".

1100
00:59:31,165 --> 00:59:34,157
- I see that.
- It was my idea.

1101
00:59:34,235 --> 00:59:36,362
Thank you, Timothy.

1102
00:59:36,437 --> 00:59:38,905
Thank you, everybody.
This is really nice.

1103
00:59:38,973 --> 00:59:42,636
But I just don't think
I'm cut out for this.

1104
00:59:42,710 --> 00:59:43,836
Elle, we have a plan.

1105
00:59:43,911 --> 00:59:46,539
Two words for you--
Discharge petition.

1106
00:59:46,614 --> 00:59:48,411
With a couple hundred
signatures...

1107
00:59:48,482 --> 00:59:50,416
we can spring Bruiser's Bill
from committee...

1108
00:59:50,484 --> 00:59:52,714
straight to the House floor
for a vote.

1109
00:59:52,787 --> 00:59:56,154
I don't know.
That sounds really complicated.

1110
00:59:56,223 --> 00:59:57,656
You've come
farther than any of us...

1111
00:59:57,725 --> 00:59:59,852
while maintaining
your bounce and sparkle.

1112
00:59:59,927 --> 01:00:01,588
We never sparkle.

1113
01:00:01,662 --> 01:00:04,756
None of us thought one person
could make a difference...

1114
01:00:04,832 --> 01:00:06,993
until you came along.

1115
01:00:08,402 --> 01:00:12,099
If I remember correctly,
isn't that 218 signatures?

1116
01:00:12,173 --> 01:00:14,573
It's not that hard.

1117
01:00:14,642 --> 01:00:17,110
Yeah.

1118
01:00:18,412 --> 01:00:19,572
Yeah.

1119
01:00:20,748 --> 01:00:22,943
I guess I know women
with more shoes than that.

1120
01:00:23,017 --> 01:00:26,214
Wait, that's me.

1121
01:00:26,287 --> 01:00:28,187
Elle...

1122
01:00:28,255 --> 01:00:30,917
it's time to finish
what you started.

1123
01:00:34,762 --> 01:00:36,559
OK, people,
a lot on the agenda today.

1124
01:00:36,630 --> 01:00:39,565
Reenie, I'm still waiting on
those one-minute floor speeches.

1125
01:00:39,633 --> 01:00:43,626
Timothy, I need recon on that
campaign finance reform hearing.

1126
01:00:43,704 --> 01:00:46,400
Grace, status meeting
in my office right away.

1127
01:00:49,844 --> 01:00:53,336
I said now.

1128
01:00:57,318 --> 01:00:58,512
Where's my staff?

1129
01:00:58,586 --> 01:01:01,714
They quit, without notice.

1130
01:01:01,789 --> 01:01:03,848
Why?

1131
01:01:05,326 --> 01:01:08,261
Marks and Hauser
just filed a petition...

1132
01:01:08,329 --> 01:01:09,728
to discharge Bruiser's Bill.

1133
01:01:09,797 --> 01:01:12,061
I'm pretty sure
that's where your staff is...

1134
01:01:12,133 --> 01:01:14,829
led by their commander
Sorority Sue.

1135
01:01:19,040 --> 01:01:23,443
Petition to discharge HR 2652,
aka Bruiser's Bill...

1136
01:01:23,511 --> 01:01:25,479
carried with no objections.

1137
01:01:25,546 --> 01:01:29,505
The petition is filed
and available for signature.

1138
01:01:30,818 --> 01:01:33,013
Actually, we are strictly...

1139
01:01:33,087 --> 01:01:36,488
"bring your own"
on the discharge petition.

1140
01:01:43,431 --> 01:01:46,958
But it's pink... and scented.

1141
01:01:47,034 --> 01:01:50,435
Gives it something extra,
don't you think?

1142
01:01:50,504 --> 01:01:52,995
We've both signed it,
as you can see.

1143
01:01:54,241 --> 01:01:56,505
I believe we're being dismissed.
Thank you.

1144
01:01:56,577 --> 01:01:58,772
There will be others
to come and sign.

1145
01:01:58,846 --> 01:02:00,939
- Don't you like pink?
- Come on!

1146
01:02:15,930 --> 01:02:18,899
Up on your feet, people.

1147
01:02:18,966 --> 01:02:21,730
Discharge petition time.

1148
01:02:21,802 --> 01:02:23,201
Upsy-daisy.

1149
01:02:25,639 --> 01:02:28,403
We have our work
cut out for us. Let's go.

1150
01:02:30,811 --> 01:02:34,247
OK, we have two signatures.
216 to go.

1151
01:02:34,315 --> 01:02:35,805
I'll break up the country
into color codes.

1152
01:02:35,883 --> 01:02:37,817
Timothy, you're teal.

1153
01:02:37,885 --> 01:02:40,080
Reena, you're magenta.

1154
01:02:40,154 --> 01:02:42,418
And Elle is marigold.

1155
01:02:42,490 --> 01:02:43,980
And I've got
the Wellington covered.

1156
01:02:44,058 --> 01:02:45,855
37 signatures in residence.

1157
01:02:45,926 --> 01:02:48,622
Sid Post, 37.

1158
01:02:48,696 --> 01:02:51,688
Congress adjourns in 3 weeks.
We can't do this alone.

1159
01:02:51,765 --> 01:02:53,699
That's why I'm calling in
reinforcements.

1160
01:02:53,767 --> 01:02:55,029
I hope we're talking...

1161
01:02:55,102 --> 01:02:57,434
the brightest political
minds in the country.

1162
01:02:59,840 --> 01:03:01,535
We're here!

1163
01:03:07,114 --> 01:03:08,706
Oh, my God!

1164
01:03:11,185 --> 01:03:13,517
Oh, gosh, we can't wait
to see the Mall.

1165
01:03:13,587 --> 01:03:15,111
And the Statue of Liberty.

1166
01:03:15,189 --> 01:03:17,589
Everybody, these are
my Delta Nu sisters.

1167
01:03:17,658 --> 01:03:19,250
This is Margot and Serena.

1168
01:03:19,326 --> 01:03:22,887
Josh made the cruise boat
pull over in Puerto Vallarta.

1169
01:03:22,963 --> 01:03:24,294
I left L.A.
Right after landing...

1170
01:03:24,365 --> 01:03:26,993
a lateral split in
the third quarter dance break.

1171
01:03:27,067 --> 01:03:29,797
It was awesome.
I went "Yah!" and "Haah!"

1172
01:03:29,870 --> 01:03:32,361
- That's so great.
- Yeah, thanks.

1173
01:03:32,439 --> 01:03:34,964
So, is it time?

1174
01:03:35,042 --> 01:03:37,237
Oh, no, it's not time yet.

1175
01:03:41,649 --> 01:03:44,413
Hello? You're here?

1176
01:03:44,485 --> 01:03:47,477
We'll meet you in the lobby.
Let's go.

1177
01:03:50,891 --> 01:03:52,950
Everybody, this is
the final member of our team...

1178
01:03:53,027 --> 01:03:54,153
Paulette Parcelle.

1179
01:03:54,228 --> 01:03:57,197
Who's ready to discharge?

1180
01:03:57,264 --> 01:04:01,928
And proposition a bill
and... whatever.

1181
01:04:02,002 --> 01:04:04,129
Let's hit the Hill.

1182
01:04:05,372 --> 01:04:07,897
If I could have
a moment of your time--

1183
01:04:07,975 --> 01:04:10,876
You could consider something--

1184
01:04:10,945 --> 01:04:13,743
Quadrant 4, corridor 6,
have lost one.

1185
01:04:15,649 --> 01:04:18,641
Sorry. How are you?

1186
01:04:18,719 --> 01:04:19,947
If I could have a minute
of your time?

1187
01:04:20,020 --> 01:04:21,954
Reena, how are you?

1188
01:04:22,022 --> 01:04:23,512
Has anybody told you
about Bruiser's Bill?

1189
01:04:23,591 --> 01:04:25,252
Is it trivial,
Congressman Hannenfeld?

1190
01:04:25,326 --> 01:04:27,317
Animals don't have
the same reactions...

1191
01:04:27,394 --> 01:04:28,520
to drugs that humans do.

1192
01:04:28,596 --> 01:04:29,722
It's like the time...

1193
01:04:29,797 --> 01:04:31,321
my trainer's sister's
cousin's girlfriend...

1194
01:04:31,398 --> 01:04:32,922
gave her overweight Yorkie
some phen-fen...

1195
01:04:33,000 --> 01:04:34,592
because she was
a little bit fat...

1196
01:04:34,668 --> 01:04:36,067
and it gained three pounds.

1197
01:04:36,136 --> 01:04:38,570
Desired result?
I don't think so.

1198
01:04:38,639 --> 01:04:40,766
You know?

1199
01:04:42,543 --> 01:04:45,137
Oh, my dear, gifted woman...

1200
01:04:45,212 --> 01:04:46,474
you tell that Bruiser Woods...

1201
01:04:46,547 --> 01:04:49,209
he can count on
the Sunshine State.

1202
01:04:49,283 --> 01:04:51,444
Thank you, Ohio.

1203
01:05:01,161 --> 01:05:03,425
Thank you, Atlanta!

1204
01:05:03,497 --> 01:05:05,294
Who's next?

1205
01:05:05,366 --> 01:05:06,856
You're next!

1206
01:05:09,403 --> 01:05:11,837
We're gonna do it.

1207
01:05:18,045 --> 01:05:19,512
Serena...

1208
01:05:19,580 --> 01:05:22,845
why do they keep
sending us to Room 216?

1209
01:05:22,916 --> 01:05:25,885
"Intern Orientation."

1210
01:05:27,321 --> 01:05:29,414
Margot, you're a genius.

1211
01:05:29,490 --> 01:05:30,957
If this doesn't get
more signatures...

1212
01:05:31,025 --> 01:05:32,185
I don't know what will.

1213
01:05:34,628 --> 01:05:37,529
Intern class of 2003 on deck!

1214
01:05:43,671 --> 01:05:46,003
Remember, flexibility counts.

1215
01:05:49,677 --> 01:05:52,237
Ready? OK!

1216
01:05:53,480 --> 01:05:55,505
Dogs of the world unite!

1217
01:06:21,442 --> 01:06:23,103
2... 4... 6... 8!

1218
01:06:23,177 --> 01:06:25,475
Sign the petition, win a date!

1219
01:06:25,546 --> 01:06:28,447
Go Bruiser's Bill, go!

1220
01:06:31,051 --> 01:06:32,575
Well, I'm signing.

1221
01:06:34,455 --> 01:06:37,481
Yes, Bob,
I know what you're reading.

1222
01:06:37,558 --> 01:06:40,356
Are you kidding?

1223
01:06:40,427 --> 01:06:43,396
Your support has been
invaluable to me.

1224
01:06:43,464 --> 01:06:46,194
If it weren't for you,
I'd be painting my own posters.

1225
01:06:46,266 --> 01:06:49,531
I don't care
if she has two weeks left.

1226
01:06:49,603 --> 01:06:51,298
She could have two years left.

1227
01:06:51,372 --> 01:06:52,930
She won't pull this off.

1228
01:06:53,006 --> 01:06:58,444
I will not be outmaneuvered
by this silly little blonde.

1229
01:07:00,214 --> 01:07:02,739
Don't worry, Bob.
I'll get her...

1230
01:07:02,816 --> 01:07:05,011
and her little dog, too.

1231
01:07:06,553 --> 01:07:08,282
Even with
the entire Wellington...

1232
01:07:08,355 --> 01:07:10,983
and 68 life-changing haircuts
under Paulette's belt...

1233
01:07:11,058 --> 01:07:12,184
we're still not even close.

1234
01:07:12,259 --> 01:07:13,988
We got a problem here.

1235
01:07:14,061 --> 01:07:17,224
The bad news is...

1236
01:07:17,297 --> 01:07:19,265
Reena.

1237
01:07:28,242 --> 01:07:32,372
Wow. You look amazing.

1238
01:07:32,446 --> 01:07:35,381
It's just layers
and highlights...

1239
01:07:35,449 --> 01:07:37,007
and a cellulose
finishing rinse.

1240
01:07:37,084 --> 01:07:38,949
I did it.

1241
01:07:39,019 --> 01:07:41,044
Cool.

1242
01:07:41,121 --> 01:07:42,782
What is the bad news?

1243
01:07:42,856 --> 01:07:45,825
We lost Hannenfeld.
We were planning on him...

1244
01:07:45,893 --> 01:07:48,293
to bring Felsen, Parks,
and Janowitz on board.

1245
01:07:48,362 --> 01:07:50,455
What are you talking about?
I talked to Hannenfeld myself.

1246
01:07:50,531 --> 01:07:52,999
I confirmed with his aide
this morning over breakfast.

1247
01:07:53,066 --> 01:07:56,194
I don't know. Somebody must've
got to him at lunch.

1248
01:07:57,237 --> 01:07:58,670
It's Grace.

1249
01:07:58,739 --> 01:08:01,333
- Please make sure.
- I will. Two weeks?

1250
01:08:01,408 --> 01:08:03,171
I'm looking for Grace Rossiter.

1251
01:08:03,243 --> 01:08:06,007
I just want to know
if she's coming back soon.

1252
01:08:06,079 --> 01:08:08,206
Elle. Hi.

1253
01:08:08,282 --> 01:08:09,510
Oh, hi.

