I give you Ms. Elle Woods.

1503
01:22:36,082 --> 01:22:37,982
It's all yours.

1504
01:22:42,422 --> 01:22:44,390
Thank you, Congresswoman.

1505
01:22:46,025 --> 01:22:48,425
Hello, everyone,
my name is Elle Woods...

1506
01:22:48,494 --> 01:22:51,292
and I'm here
to speak to you today...

1507
01:22:51,364 --> 01:22:55,061
about a piece of legislation
called Bruiser's Bill.

1508
01:23:05,578 --> 01:23:08,138
But you know...

1509
01:23:08,214 --> 01:23:11,445
today is supposed to be
about education.

1510
01:23:11,517 --> 01:23:15,954
So instead, I want to tell you
about the education...

1511
01:23:16,022 --> 01:23:18,149
you all have given me
over the past three months.

1512
01:23:18,224 --> 01:23:20,124
What about Bruiser's Bill?
We still need 15 signatures.

1513
01:23:20,193 --> 01:23:21,421
She's blowing it.

1514
01:23:21,494 --> 01:23:24,486
I came to Washington
to help my dog Bruiser...

1515
01:23:24,564 --> 01:23:25,997
and somewhere
along the way...

1516
01:23:26,065 --> 01:23:29,967
I learned
a really unexpected lesson.

1517
01:23:31,270 --> 01:23:34,535
I know what you're thinking--
Who is this girl?

1518
01:23:34,607 --> 01:23:37,872
And what could this simple,
small-town girl from Bel Air...

1519
01:23:37,944 --> 01:23:41,072
have to say to all of us?
I'll tell you.

1520
01:23:41,147 --> 01:23:45,413
It's about something
that's bigger than me...

1521
01:23:45,485 --> 01:23:48,579
or any single act
of legislation.

1522
01:23:48,654 --> 01:23:51,714
This is about a matter
that should be at...

1523
01:23:51,791 --> 01:23:55,488
the highest importance
to every American--

1524
01:23:56,629 --> 01:23:59,029
My hair.

1525
01:24:01,534 --> 01:24:02,967
There's this salon
in Beverly Hills.

1526
01:24:03,035 --> 01:24:06,835
It's really fancy and beautiful.

1527
01:24:06,906 --> 01:24:08,840
It's impossible
to get an appointment.

1528
01:24:08,908 --> 01:24:11,240
Unless you're Julia Roberts
or from "Friends"...

1529
01:24:11,310 --> 01:24:12,971
you can just forget it.

1530
01:24:13,045 --> 01:24:16,845
But one day, they called me.
They had an opening.

1531
01:24:16,916 --> 01:24:19,180
So I was going to finally
get the chance...

1532
01:24:19,252 --> 01:24:21,379
to sit in one of
those sacred beauty chairs.

1533
01:24:21,454 --> 01:24:23,445
I was so excited.

1534
01:24:23,523 --> 01:24:26,651
Then the colorist...

1535
01:24:26,726 --> 01:24:30,025
gave me Brassy Brigitte
instead of Harlow Honey.

1536
01:24:30,096 --> 01:24:34,226
The shampoo girl washed my hair
with spiral perm solution...

1537
01:24:34,300 --> 01:24:37,292
instead of color-intensive
moisturizing shampoo.

1538
01:24:37,370 --> 01:24:40,567
Finally, the stylist...

1539
01:24:40,640 --> 01:24:44,838
gave me a bob... with bangs.

1540
01:24:45,878 --> 01:24:49,405
Suffice to say,
it was just wrong.

1541
01:24:49,482 --> 01:24:54,078
All wrong. For me, you know?

1542
01:24:54,153 --> 01:24:55,518
First I was angry.

1543
01:24:55,588 --> 01:24:59,046
And then I realized my anger
was completely misdirected.

1544
01:24:59,125 --> 01:25:01,184
This wasn't the salon's fault.

1545
01:25:01,260 --> 01:25:03,956
I had sat there and
witnessed this injustice...

1546
01:25:04,030 --> 01:25:05,725
and had let it happen.

1547
01:25:05,798 --> 01:25:10,565
I didn't get involved
in the process.

1548
01:25:10,636 --> 01:25:14,367
I forgot to use my voice.

1549
01:25:14,440 --> 01:25:18,536
I forgot to believe in myself.

1550
01:25:18,611 --> 01:25:20,875
But now I know better.

1551
01:25:20,947 --> 01:25:27,011
I know that one honest voice
can be louder than a crowd.

1552
01:25:27,086 --> 01:25:31,921
I know that
if we lose our voice...

1553
01:25:31,991 --> 01:25:35,722
or if we let those
who speak on our behalf...

1554
01:25:35,795 --> 01:25:38,423
compromise our voice...

1555
01:25:38,498 --> 01:25:42,662
then, this country...

1556
01:25:42,735 --> 01:25:45,499
this country is in
for a really bad haircut.

1557
01:25:50,142 --> 01:25:52,474
So speak up, America.

1558
01:25:52,545 --> 01:25:54,103
Speak up!

1559
01:25:54,180 --> 01:25:57,581
Speak up for the home
of the brave.

1560
01:25:57,650 --> 01:26:01,279
Speak up for the land
of the free gift with purchase.

1561
01:26:01,354 --> 01:26:05,916
Speak up, America. Speak up!

1562
01:26:08,761 --> 01:26:10,695
And remember...

1563
01:26:10,763 --> 01:26:12,856
you are beautiful.

1564
01:26:16,769 --> 01:26:18,361
Thank you.

1565
01:26:32,184 --> 01:26:33,811
Thank you.

1566
01:26:33,886 --> 01:26:36,446
Everyone, it's time I spoke up.

1567
01:26:36,522 --> 01:26:38,820
I think Timothy's smoking!

1568
01:26:43,796 --> 01:26:46,321
I'm married.

1569
01:26:48,234 --> 01:26:49,531
Thank you.

1570
01:27:40,419 --> 01:27:44,150
You didn't! Thank you!

1571
01:27:44,223 --> 01:27:45,713
Thank you!

1572
01:27:48,761 --> 01:27:49,887
Thank you.

1573
01:27:49,962 --> 01:27:53,193
What is this? Oh, my God!

1574
01:27:54,467 --> 01:27:56,059
That's so perfect!

1575
01:28:22,094 --> 01:28:24,927
This week,
Congresswoman Libby Hauser...

1576
01:28:24,997 --> 01:28:27,363
finished decorating
her house...

1577
01:28:27,433 --> 01:28:29,367
sent her son off to college...

1578
01:28:29,435 --> 01:28:31,494
and negotiated a settlement...

1579
01:28:31,570 --> 01:28:33,800
between the San Antonio
labor unions...

1580
01:28:33,873 --> 01:28:36,103
and the Department
of Sanitation.

1581
01:28:36,175 --> 01:28:38,803
Snaps for Congresswoman Hauser!

1582
01:29:26,225 --> 01:29:28,819
Now that we're married,
where do you want to live?

1583
01:29:28,894 --> 01:29:31,522
Beverly Hills? Boston?
Washington?

1584
01:29:31,597 --> 01:29:34,828
- I know just the place.
- Yeah?

